76561198035983319,Recommended,220240,12939518,"Posted: 14 November, 2014",all,Reaver,"Price (regular): $29.99 ($39.99 for deluxe)Price (lowest): $7.49 (75% off)My overall rating: 9.5/10Easily one of my favorite games of all time.Value: 9/10Most other games this age are already down to $20, however the singleplayer is a lot longer than most other action/shooter games, making it well worth the price.Singleplayer: 10/10Amazing singleplayer. Capturing outposts is probably the best part. There are over 30 spread over the massive map. The main story has some pretty good action too. Plus there is hunting, racing, and assassination side missions and a lot of other things that are a lot of fun.Co-op: 5/10 (2-4 players)Co-op has some serious issues. When the match tries to launch it almost always crashes or freezes when loading. Due to this you wont be able to find players unless you are playing with friends. When it works it is decent but doesnt have the openness that makes far cry great. Update: co-op has been working better lately.Multiplayer: 6.5/10The multiplayer is actually pretty good, but a little generic. Doesn't have enough players to reach its full potential though.Content: 9.5/10Both the co-op and multiplayer are pretty basic, but the singleplayer makes up for it. You of course have the story and outposts, but there is also tons of ruins and caves to be explored for relics and loot, side missions, trials, races, dlc missions, and even knife throwing and poker.Length: 10/10An average playthrough of the singleplayer will take you roughly 30 hours, doing the main storyline capturing all the outposts and doing most of the side missions.Story: 8/10The story really tries to be great and in some ways it is but also is a little flat. You and your friends are having the time of your life until getting caught by slavers on a remote island. You escape and have to save your friends and liberate the natives from the pirates in the process.Gameplay: 10/10Very good, open gameplay. Most situations you can choose to attack however you like. Climb any mountain for a good vantage point with a sniper rifle, use stealth with a bow and using knife takedowns, attack head on with an lmg, or charge in with a truck with c4 planted on it.With freinds: 6/10The co-op and multiplayer are pretty fun with friends but doesnt have a lot of substance.Graphics: 9/10Good graphics, very good considering the scale of the game.Physics: 9.5/10Maybe not as smooth walking around a small area and shooting a few people as call of duty, but all in all the physics are a lot better than just about any other game. Driving really feels good. Good fire physics, you can light large areas of brush with a flamethrower.Performance: 9/10Works good for the most part. Can easily play it on max setting with my laptop, core i7 4810mq @ 2.80 GHz (turbo to 3.80 GHz) 12gbs ram and gtx870m 3gbs dedicated. Haven't had any notable issues or bugs.Sound: 8/10Sound is good but maybe a little rough here and there.Polished: 8/10Nothing majorly wrong with it but it does have the usual trees growing through rocks and animals spawning inside stuff.Atmosphere: 8.5/10The vast landscape gives you a good immersive feel but could be better if they didn't have so much of the same plants making it all feel the same.Objectives: 7/10Objectives are pretty basic. Pretty much go fight through these people and do (insert objective here). Some are a little more in depth.Clarity: 9/10No problems with knowing where to go or what to do. The story line is linear and very easy to follow.World: 9.5/10Unparalleled world. Massive world with large mountains, caves, ruins, shanty towns, vast foliage, ocean, and tons of wildlife to try and kill you. Although most of the landscape has the same trees and plants so a lot of it looks the same.Characters: 8/10The characters are interesting. The antagonists really make you want to kill them. All the characters are just a little thin but still good.UI: 6.5/10The menus are pretty poor. Pulling up your map is really slow. All other menus are in the escape menu which is pretty slow and not that great to navigate. Plus there's Uplay which is horrible.Controls: 9/10Mostly standard controls. Not my favorite layout but close enough I didn't feel the need to change anything.Freedom: 10/10As much freedom as you could ask for. You can ignor your current mission to go off capturing outpost, doing side mission, or just go for a nature hike.Influence: 2.5/10The story itself is very linear. Only choice in the game is the ending and what happens after.Settings: 9/10Four difficulty setting so good for most any skill level. Average control options.Character progression: 6/10Sometimes feels like they resticked what you can do at the beginning instead of allowing you to do more later on.Weapon selection: 9/10Has plenty of weapons. Handguns, SMGs, assault rifles, shotguns, LMGs, sniper rifles, launchers, explosives, and specials. Over 30 total, though some feel similar.Customization: 7/10Most weapons can be modded. Higher level guns can have up to 3 mods. Mods incude extended mags, silencers, and several types of sights, though most guns are limited on which mods are available. Almost all weapons can be painted.AI: 8.5/10For the most part the ai is fairly intelegent. Considering what they have to do in an open world unrelated to a story, it's very good. Though this causes a few quirks.Up to date: 9/10Only came out at the end of 2012 and there isn't any notable aging to the game. Not lacking anything that newer games might have.Replayability: 8.5/10The story doesnt give incentive replay it, but since you can whatever you like however you like, the rest of the game has a lot of replay value.Pace: 8.5/10For such a long game the balance between length and action is very good. You can go straight to the next mission, rush through a few outposts, or take your time doing everything at your own pace.Repetitiveness: 8/10If you were to just walk up with an assault rifle everytime it would probably get very repetitive, but change up your approach everytime and it won't be much at all.Realism: 8.5/10It has some good aspects and a few poor ones when it comes to how realistic it is. Even compared to other games the amount of people you are able to kill is a little ridiculous. It has some supernatural elements which isn't bad but they are a little lame and seem to be inspired by acid trips. Other than that it's actually got good physics and overall better than most games.DLC: 5/10The downloadable content is all pretty mediocre. A few independent short story missions that are okay, some co-op and multiplayer content, and a few other things that are all insignificant.Achievements: 6/1050 achievements but only on Uplay not Steam, and 6 are for co-op making them near impossible. The rest of the achievements are great. Good amount and some challenging but nothing too hard.Trading cards: N/ADoesn't have Steam badges/trading cards.Series improvement: 10/10Far Cry 2 was a good game, however has aged a lot and lacked in a few aspects. Far Cry 3 did a great job at improving and made a very well rounded, good performing game.Originality: 10/10Bottom line is that no other game is very much like Far Cry. Maybe slightly similar to games like Just Cause or some RPGs and it may have some Tomb Raider elements but not enough that its overall gameplay is at all the same as anything else."
,Recommended,220240,32645920,Posted: 22 June,all,Bash,"I will only review the singleplayer aspect of the game.I played through acrackeddifferent version of the game before, in case you were wondering about my playtime. Nevertheless, I felt the need to buy this game for real, although it uses the Ubisoft's Uplay in addition to Steams DRM.My ImpressionDefinitely one of my favorite games - a perfect mix of a beautiful environment worth exploring, amazing storytelling and enjoyable gameplay.TL;DRA quick definition of insanity for all you party people:PositiveMediocreNegative+ Amazing Storytelling~ not a strong story+ scattered letters telling a story of their own+ Beautiful island+ Absolutely masterful villain~ weak allies+ Good character development~ feels out of place sometimes+ Fun gameplay+ Paragliding over the landscape+ Stunning graphicsThe StoryYou are Jason Brody, partying with your friends and family to celebrate your little brother attaining his pilot's license.However, things aren't going to be all fun and games as you are kidnapped by pirates and will be seeing death before finally escaping their claws.You happen to be saved by the natives of the island, the Rakyat, and for them to help you rescue your friends, you have to do them a favor, too. Consequently, you leave the face of the rich kid behind and set out to become a savior, a warrior, and an avenger.If this setting didn't sound like it could be fun for you, let me tell you that this game shines through its storytelling - sadly saying anything more would be a spoiler.Additionally, don't fret about buying a short game - completing the story with all it has to offer, may take up to a good 40h.The WorldAs the destination of this little vacation, you chose a tropical island, somewhere in the middle of the sea.The island offers you a great variety of wildlife, that you can choose to hunt - but be wary that some of these animals prefer to be the hunter instead of the hunted.Moreover, the geography is just great - there is a lot of vertical movement that can be done and if you are lucky you will find some kind of glider atop a hill and be equipped to fly miles across the island.The CharactersJason Brody - there isn't much known regarding the background of the protagonist, however from the little intro sequence and the appearance of his family it looks like he grew up well hidden from the wicked of the globe, with nothing to care about in the world.Friends and Family - your little and big brother, girlfriend and some more sidekicks. Saying that, I intend it the way it sounds like, you never really get to know a lot about the relationship between you and all the others, which left me not really caring about them.Dennis - he is one of the Rakyat, your savior and the one who could see the warrior in you, he seems like a chill guy, and his tattoo drawing skills are top notch.Citra - the leader of the tribe, she is a special woman but has only her and her tribe’s best in mind. She wants power more than anything.Thats not to say that every character in the game is bad or weak. There are interesting and fun  ones, however, I can't mention them here without spoiling the fun. Let's just say, some will speak a little german...Vaas - this is the one you have been anticipating. If a game makes you care more about the villain than any other character - it did something damn right. Vaas is absolutely mother♥♥♥♥ing crazy - and you will love it.The GameplayIt's a first person shooter, nothing special in that regard.However, the stealth aspect with its melee takedowns is so satisfying and combined with your environment and all the things to do and sites to go to the gameplay really shines.Throughout the island, there are communication towers scattered, which you can climb to extend the map and gain access to new weapons.Speaking of weapons -the variety is greatand you can even customize them with skins, which has a cool feel to it.Other than that the pirates have set up camp in various places around the island and you can conquer them guns blazing or eliminate every single person without them knowing what hit them.The latter will give you, aside from your feeling of accomplishment, bonusexperienceand won't trigger the alarm for enemy reinforcement.Should you have been surprised at the word ""experience"" - yes, there is a skill tree which grants you cool new abilities - like being able to take down multiple enemies from above or under water.Last but not least you can also craft various items, most importantly syringes used for health recovery in combat.The VisualsThe game is powered by theDunia Engine, if this doesn't ring a bell, saying it's a derivative of theCryEngineshould.That being said - the game looks incredible. Let alone the setting on a tropical island, the deep, dense jungle, extending into bright beaches and ending into the crystal clear, blue ocean.Perhaps sun reflected on the water is just one of my personal obsessions, but it looks just so incredible.The SoundIt's really good - you hear pirates screaming around the island; yourself mumbling things, which really enhance the feeling of character progression and the wildlife around in the jungle sounds amazingly terrifying.Weapon sounds seem good; moving through high grass and leaves appears realistic and cutting into flesh is pleasing, to say the least.Ultimately, let me just say this - burning down fields of weed with a flamethrower to dubstep powered bySkrillexis definitely memorable.The VerdictDo yourself a favor and try this game, it doesn't matter if you are not a fan of first person shooters, or if the story doesn't call home to you at first.This is one of the best games I know of and you can see the size of my library ;-)NoteIf you have read this far -thank you.I hope this review helped you in deciding to buy this game and if it did, I would be grateful for a 'thumbs up', if you didn't like it, you can give me a 'thumbs down' but I would be glad to hear your opinion on what you didn't like."
