76561198061432657,Recommended,220240,23247287,"Posted: 27 May, 2016",all,RicketyCricket,"Doesn't Play Nice With Windows 10This is a very good game. Still looks good, even today. A competant story (that eventually runs out of steam hard toward the end), and at this point an iconic villian. Fun gameplay and will run like butter on most modern systems.Oh hello there windows 10, care to screw it all up?So yeah at least in my case and a couple other forum users, Windows 10 made launching this game a nightmare. Either it wont launch through steam at all or it will immediately crash. Here's what you do:Go to your folder for the game, for example:C: > Program Files 86 > Steam > Steamapps > Common > Far Cry 3 > binRight Click on farcry3_d3d11.exe (not farcry3.exe), go to properties > compatibility and set it to windows 7 (8 may work too but i use 7). Then launch THAT executable and only that one. Should work fine then.If you're willing to deal with that headache, then it's still a great game."
,Not Recommended,220240,18008229,"Posted: 12 September, 2015",all,GJeebus,"The game itself is enjoyable, but I can no longer play it. A couple months ago I uninstalled this game because I wasn't playing it. After installing it I can no longer access my Uplay account because Uplay wouldn't accept my password. I tried to recover my password, but Uplay refused to send me a password recovery email. I tried to get support, but in order to get Uplay support you have to log in to Uplay. I can't play anymore because Uplay won't let me log in. Thanks, Ubisoft. You truly are my greatest ally.Also if you're wondering ""Why didn't you make an account to contact support?"" Well I did, but even after a couple months I never did get that confirmation email.[No Spoilers and tl;dr at the bottom]Edit: After numerous comments asking me to change my review to positive, I've decided to go in-depth as to what I think about the game. I'd advise you to take my opinions with a grain of salt because I haven't been able to play the game in about a year. As for the game itself I would say that it's enjoyable at best. The story isn't interesting in the slightest, but the occasions when Vaas shows up can be quite entertaining. I would say that Vaas was the only reason the story slightly interested me at all because I didn't care at all about my friends. Why would I considering they weren't developed enough for me to even care? Without spoilers the ending gives 2 choices that you have to make on the spot and none of them effect anything. They're not satisfying and the only reason there are 2 choices is because you gotta have that variety right? Anyways I don't think that the story is the reason people play Far Cry 3, because the game is more focused towards free-roam. The world is big, but there isn't much to do. You can hunt, do some side missions, take down enemy outposts, pick flowers, find some collectables, but that's about it. There isn't much going on around you so it makes the world feel empty. I don't remember seeing many animals besides a couple of herds and a few lone panthers. When you take down an outpost the enemies stop spawning in the area, which makes sense, but it makes that area far more boring and almost usless in terms of replay value. One thing they did to fix this is that you can reset the outposts when they're all overtaken. It's a much appreciated feature that should add a lot of replay value if you've enjoyed the main game. There is around 4 weapons for each class (Snipers, pistols, rifles and such) and some special weapons, but most of the common weapons are just generic. A few good examples of the less generic weapons are the A2000, U100, Flamethrower, and BZ19. Shooting in this game shouldn't be that interesting, but it feels much more satisfying due to the fantastic animations. One last thing I liked is that you can customize if you want to go in with a stealthy or more explosive approach. The game gives you a lot of options if we're talking about how you want to approach enemies.I'd say if you want to have a game you can play sometimes and have a bit of fun go ahead and buy this one. If I remember correctly there is co-op so that might be fun with your friends. I've never tried it, but it might be worth a shot. Twenty dollars isn't too bad of a price, but at that price you're better off getting Deus Ex: Human Revolution, Bioshock 1, Rainbow Six Vegas 2, Insurgency, Fallout New Vegas, Splinter Cell Choas Theory, or Far Cry 3 Blood Dragon (I like the atmosphere and weapons in Blood Dragon more than 3 because it feels a lot more unique. Also it has laser guns + lazer lizards) If you want a free-roam jungle fps I don't know any others besides Far Cry 3, so if you want to play this game specifically for that reason alone it wouldn't be too bad of an idea to get this. If you want this for the story just look it up on Youtube. If you want this just for Vaas, refer to my previous statement.tl;dr: Get it if you want a free-roam fps jungle game. The story sucks, Vass is kind of cool, and the free roam and variety of approaches may be the deal breaker for you. It's all right as a free-roam game, but don't expect to be blown away at all or interested for more than 20 hours. There is co-op but I can't say anything about that since I haven't played it. It might be worth a try with your friends."
