76561198003026615,Recommended,220240,29347293,Posted: 18 January,all,RivaL[.]ReNeGaDe,"Far Cry 3 is an action packed adventure. You have multiple objectives you can do and they don’t have to be done in order or you can simply never do them! You can find relics, raid outposts, explore, find treasure chests, and many more endeavors within Far Cry 3. The campaign reminds me of college students on vacation and things go south and rather rapidly. I don’t want to spoil anything, but the story itself contains mysteries, mystical happenings, and a crazy adventure that won’t leave a bad taste behind like other action adventure titles.The game itself is open world and both islands are living, breathing entities. Whether its people driving around, guards patrolling, or a lion prowling in the tall grasses of the jungle, there is always some form of activity going on in the background or around you. To explore this vast world, one can obtain ATVs, vehicles, boats or air gliders and enjoy the beautiful scenery of the Rook Islands. The scenery has lush jungles, waterfalls, white sandy beaches, clear blue waters, swamps, and green grasslands. The developers put a lot of thought in this game and it seems they added a bit of every biome in this title.You’ll notice outposts and telecommunication towers – the outposts provide you with a means of fast travel, a place to sell/buy items, and local militia to fight near your proximity. The telecommunication towers help you reveal large portions of the map so you can prioritize your next adventure or continue your way on the campaign. There are a few factions on the islands, but I won’t go into them since they may or may not be a spoiler (I’d rather be safe than sorry).With any open world game there is customization or crafting (most of the time) and this game delivers, even though it is on a smaller scale than other titles. Your crafting consists of killing wildlife and using their hides to make a bigger holster, a bigger ammo bag, etc. in order to obtain more items (ammo, syringes, etc.). You can customize guns (paint, scope, magazine, etc.), but don’t assume the customization is big compared to Battlefield titles or other shooting games. They do bare bones on customization with guns, but they do improve a big portion of the stats relating to the gun (aim, ammo capacity, range, etc.). They could have added more customization/crafting options in the game, but I did like the quests that one must obtain to maximize their crafting potential.The UI was clunky at times; I’d have to press multiple times of ESC to get back to the game as one example. The game was well enough to ignore the clunkiness of the UI and the game has a few years on it, so it isn’t ‘modernized’. I didn’t have any FPS drops or bottlenecking when playing this title. I never experienced any crashes or delays or audible problems that sounded off or distant. The voices were done in a way to have an emotional experience and trying to connect with the player when going through the campaign and experiencing the hardships from protagonist, his friends, and his enemies.A title like Far Cry 3 needs no spoilers and I truly think most people who like action adventure games will enjoy this title. I might not have done everything (finding relics, treasure, etc.), but I did finish the campaign and I would recommend this title to anyone. There are still a lot of content for me to finish, so this game is worth its price."
