,Recommended,220240,34378876,Posted: 20 August,all,Baines,"I will only review the single-player aspect of the gameFar Cry 3. The third installment in the Far Cry franchise, although old (two new ones out as of yet) this game is still relevant, which is rare for a title over 5 years old. Far Cry 3 offers an experience unlike its predecessors and other games on the market. Present or past.Pros:Map: Far Cry 3 is set on a tropical island in the north/south Pacific ocean (not sure ¯\_(ツ)_/¯ ). The map is amazing, and extremely large offering hours of extra content after the campaign.Characters: All the main/side characters are brilliantly voice acted and seem realistic, towards the end, you begin to actually care about all the characters, bad or good.The antagonist(s): Well... Vass... He's amazing. You actually believe this guy is fukn insane! He's brilliantly voice acted, all his missions are entertaining and every time you think you have finally caught him he throws another curve ball. Don't believe me? He won ""Best New Character"" at the Canadian Videogame Award.Yep, Vass is an antagonist! - However, just play the game, to figure out more.Gameplay: Hours of gameplay available, hunting, side-missions. endless forests to explore and skills to require. Enemies are enjoyable to kill.Combat: Combos are amazing. After awhile, you actually see Jason Brody get better (after unlocking skills) and it feels awesome, simultaneously killing 3 pirates with one takedown. The gunplay is fun, however sometimes feels clunky.Hunting: First time you hunt, it's cool. Finding more dangerous animals in the wild is a challenge, and you often die. It isn't super 'grindy' either, as there's a lot of animals in the world, with their dedicated zones. Making certain animals easy to find.  However, after 6-9 hours it's pretty useless.Campaign.  A. M. A. Z. I. N. G - One of my favorites, due to the characters (especially Vass)Cons:Uplay....Deaths: Sometimes death feel stupid, or you will just comm