,Recommended,220240,31013770,Posted: 8 April,all,Ja,"'Do you know the defenition of insanity?'You won't have until you play this game. It's honestly incredible. At the moment of writing this review, it's my favourite game. In my opinion, it's better than the entire Just Cause, Assassin's Creed, Halo, Call of Duty, HITMAN and the rest of the Far Crys' franchises.Characters: 9/10The Characters in this game are truly stunning. Vaas and Hoyt are terryfying villians who you won't forget any time soon. They both do thinks to you and their men which will make you wince. Jason Brody is also an intresting charcters who progresses throughout the game. Citra, Buck and Denis have great voice actors and intresting characteristics, even if they are not as fleshed out as tthe main villians and heroes.Plot and Story: 9/10The plot is pretty straight forward. It's a revenege thriller focused around a character who ,at the beginning of the game, couldn't even fire a gun. However, the story takes the plot and mixes it with great missions and intresting stories. Even though the game is a FPS, Action shooter, it's very much based around choices and philoshpy. The story is what takes Far Cry 3 to great heights.Combat: 8.5/10Combat may not be the best aspect of FC3, but it's still really fun. Liberating bases with a sniper rifle will never get old. However, combat becomes difficult with different guns. Assult Rifles do little to no damage, while a handgun kills the man instantly. Also, Headshots sometimes don't insta-kill, which is a big nusiance.Open World and Side-Missions: 9/10The Open World of FC3 is amazing. It's so vast and detailed it makes it feel like a 2015 game, not a 2012. There are so many things to do after completing the main campain; Radio Towers, Bases, Wanted: Dead, Path of the hunter, Trials of the Rakyat, Story missions, Relics, Letters of the lost, Memory Cards, Skills, etc.. And they are all really funDLC: 7/10Read my review here:http://steamcommunity.com/id/dank_code