,Recommended,220240,23960558,"Posted: 30 June, 2016",all,Randall Flagg,"Endless world FPS... Only if you like these. Continuing straight from FC2 (game char') you fight on a far away island to release your friends. While there's obviously a lot to do, single player can be over after 8 hours or less if you choose not to play any mission outside the plot. Some mission are fun, some get boring (actually, most of them are kind of repetitive in one way or the other after you play them a few times). Graphics are marvelous, and the sound is great too, but after finishing the game you feel some parts of the plot are weak, f.e. the parts where you fight bosses - you black out, all other enemies disappear... weak.The multi player was disappointing, but I really liked the Co-op (left4dead play style, with pirates instead of zombies). There are 8 missions to be played for hours, with a ladder to abilities and experience, as in any other shooter today. The Bad things in the MP are many sever disconnections, and visual bugs (like floating dead people, etc...).It's not as good as the gaming media shouted, but if you explore the whole island, buying it today for 7.49$ (in sales) , it is a money well spent.BTW, there is no reason to buy the Deluxe edition - unless you want the whole thing. It's main addition is 2 Island side missions, nothing more.7.5/10"
