,Not Recommended,220240,11014671,"Posted: 1 July, 2014",all,Mr. Meeseeks,"I've played about 30+ hours ofFar Cry 3on PC and another 40+ hours back on Xbox 360, meaning I've had quite some experience with the game. That being said,Far Cry 3is probably Ubisoft's prime example of advertising and hyping without fully delivering, hence my negative review: it's far from as great as people claim it to be.The Good:· Michael Mando's performance as Vaas Montenegro is very well done, simply one of the best motion capture in any game.· The huge island allows for hours of exploring, hunting, and doing sidemissions.The Bad:· First I'm going to list what bothers me the most, and it also happens to be the thing I liked the most... Vaas. Ubisoft promotedFar Cry 3with Vaas from the get-go; putting him in the early demo, placing him on the boxart, including a wahini-figure in the Collector's Edition... his insanity was basically the center of the game. Unfortunately, those promises weren't met. Slight spoiler warning ahead so please skip to the next point if you don't want any bits of the story given away, but Ubisoft's oh so glorious Vaas Montenegro had a combined total screentime of 15 minutes. Yep. Durning your 30+ hours, only 15 minutes will be spent looking at or listening to Vaas. It's like buying a movie ticket to go and see Fight Club just to end up watching A Good Day to Die Hard.· The missions are repetetive beyond believe. Save this person, do this for that guy, kill these guys. The sidemissions exist largely of racing- and huntingmissions, both equally boring after the first time. The only enjoyable mission -- spoiler warning, again -- was the one where you had to burn marijuanafield with a flamethrower to a raggae-dubstep beat. If only there were more original missions like those.· The character development is so unbelievable it feels parodic at times. You go from a party-going teenager to a hipster Rambo that is able to murder hundreds of experienced soldiers in a few hours.· There's no real reason to craft anything. Health syringes are useless if you have upgraded your manual healing skill that'll automatically heal you when you're out of syringes (by bandaging your scratched arm when you fall or pulling out a bullet when a tiger attacks you. Yeah...) Your wallet can only hold a certain amount of money, so maybe crafting a larger wallet would be usefull. But why do so if climbing all the radio towers will basically get you all the weapons for free?The Visuals:· The overal graphics are very nice, from detailed textures to great lighting, but the shadows were so overdone it almost felt cartoonish.Final verdict:· High expectations, even higher promises, and ultimately you get an avarage repetetive shooter.Far Cry 3is the best example of how Ubisoft spends more time hyping and advertising than polishing what could have been a much better product. 6/10"
