,Recommended,220240,10695831,"Posted: 22 June, 2014",all,DanceBicthOrDie,"Overall Far Cry 3 is a very solid First Person Shooter game. It has a very intense story that makes you want to finish the game from start to end without stopping. To note this is the first Far Cry game I have FINISHED. I could never finish the previous Far Cry games for many reasons. That being said this game in the series was very enjoyable to me. As you can see the game took me no more than 13ish hours to beat, doing some side missions and other little challenges in the game. It is a fairly easy game to get through compared to the other Far Cry games. One gameplay mechanic I really enjoyed was the stealth. It was top notch fun sneaking around taking people down with brutal machete kills. The skill system works very well with the game too. I never once felt underpowered in fact the way the game progresses you feel weak at the beginning, but towards the end of the game you are a bonafide killing machine. The story like I said was very entertaining, playing out like a classic hollywood revenge film. You play as Jason Brody a man who decides to go on a getaway vacation to a mysterious island. Things go south and your friends get captured, leaving it up to you to save them. The game has great character development showing how Jason must learn to adapt to the situation at hand and become a ruthless killer in order to save his friends. The game does feature 2 different endings each one being very different from the other. The endings were the only thing that made the game a little negative for me. Without spoiling much one of the endings is very empty meaning it feels as if it was rushed and things needed to be futher explained. Other than that it is a great single player experience. I have yet to play multiplayer. As far as technical aspects the game ran very smoothly never dropping its frame rate or crashing. I had a good experience with UPlay too. This is definitely the right step in the Far Cry series and I am now looking forward to Far Cry 4.9/10- TLDR Great game with awesome gameplay mechanics and a solid story. Looking forward to Far Cry 4!"
