,Recommended,220240,11231065,"Posted: 14 July, 2014",all,CinderellaMan,"Far Cry 3 succeeds like its predecessors in providing an open world action / thriller set in a tropical climate.  Like similar games such as GTA and Batman: AC, the current objective is shown on the map... there are side missions and mini-games that can be unlocked and played at will.  Portions of the map details are hidden until radio towers are ""unlocked"" by scaling them and sabotaging the fuse box.  Weapons and skills are steadily unlocked as progress is made in both the main story line, collecting hidden treasures, and completing various other tasks.  Thrown in for good measure are hunting and crafting, and a completely separate and very challenging co-op campaign.On the plus side:> The world is beautiful and nicely detailed.> The story is quite good and features one of the best antagonists in any video game I have ever played.> The weapons look, feel, and sound excellent.> The stronghold raids and ""kill nasty dude x"" side missions are the meat of the game and very entertaining, with many ways to approach them> The takedown skills are challenging to apply and fun when they work.> An excellent PC port with all the graphical and control flourish we expect.On the negative side:> The game ramps up too quickly... I found myself proceeding at a reasonable pace, and by act 2 I was becoming overpowered... this along with another mechanic in act 2 makes the second act seem anti-climactic.> On the same vein, the first act Boss feels more threatening than the second.  He also was such a good character I was disappointed that he was dead.  Can he have his own game, please?> The native peoples character models are too similar.> The world does not feel ""lived in""... it feels more like an action game set piece.  There is also very little variation in the game world.> There is very little incentive to continue exploring after the game ends.The co-op campaign is very difficult... you will want at least 3 players for that.  I bought the game on sale on steam for $5... was it worth it? Yes absolutely.  I would say $20 is reasonable for this since I got nearly 40 hours of entertainment out of it.8/10"
