76561198067595197,Recommended,220240,10500704,"Posted: 16 June, 2014",all,Firestorm,10/10 best game ever
,Recommended,220240,14149546,"Posted: 24 January, 2015",all,Lord Shadow Z,"This was the game of the series that I had heard the most about from reading reviews and whatnot. This is the first game where I’ve actually found real enjoyment from playing it and I’m so glad that most of my biggest issues with Far Cry 2 were extinct when I played this one. For once, I’ll actually be talking about how good the game is and just not relentlessly bash it.In this game, your character Jason Brody and his friends were on vacation and after skydiving over a random island get captured by natives/slavers. You escape and have to explore the island, rescue your friends, and help the natives, the Rakyat, deal with pirates. It’s a simple premise, but it definitely works. The island is beautiful. This is by far the best looking game in the series so far. It’s exciting to wander around seeing all the various plant life, the waterfalls, and everything else the island has to offer. It’s a gorgeous game.This is once again an open world shooter, which means you can approach missions however you like. Once the game finally gave me a sniper rifle with a silencer attachment, I was unstoppable. There are outposts you can clear of pirates all over the island, and for me, all I would do is snipe all of them and go undetected most of the time. Unlike the previous game, when you clear out an outpost, the Rakyat warriors move in and hold the outpost, and there will be fewer to no pirates spawning in the area ever again. This was one of my top 2 problems in Far Cry 2 eradicated. Awesome.The wildlife…what can I say? There’s a variety of wildlife that you can hunt, or be hunted by, for you to collect pelts to craft upgrades. The crafting system is pretty good, letting you create things to restore health, enhance senses to detect enemies or wildlife, increase ammo capacity, or carry more money. As for the wildlife, there’s goats and deer, as well as more exotic creatures like komodo dragons and tigers. Tigers are really annoying to deal with if you run into them a lot early in the game like I did, but it keeps you on your toes and keeps your twitchy trigger finger happy. If you feel slightly less adventurous, you can just hit the animals with a vehicle. This was the best method I found to reliably kill skarks, using the propeller blades of the boat to decimate them. I ended up getting most of my upgrades done pretty early in the story.There’s a couple types of side missions you can do, such as hunting rare animals, knife assassination missions, types of racing missions, and various others which I haven’t really tried. Aside from the hunting the rare animals to get all the best upgrades, I didn’t really bother with doing other side missions because they just weren’t all that interesting to me, and I got bored of them pretty quickly.There’s a skill system which is solid. You get xp from kills and missions and everything just as you would expect, and when you earn skill points from getting enough xp, you can put points into one of three skill trees to increase things like your survivability, how fast you can reload, boost accuracy, new types of takedowns, and all sorts of things. There are few skills I would call useless which makes deciding where to use skill points all that much harder.I think my only major problem with this game is that the stupid, inhumanly smart AI from both of the previous games is back, and god is it annoying. I tend to use weapons with silencers on them so that I can stealth kill from afar. Yet when I happen to miss a shot just barely, or even when I kill someone who was near another enemy, they know exactly where to look for me somehow. How? Do they just happen to automatically know the bullet trajectory? It makes sniping a little bit harder, and on one particular outpost, clearing it out this way was just impossible, and I had to clear out waves of reinforcements before finally claiming it for the Rakyat. Also, AI pixel perfect accuracy is still bull.Far Cry 3 is the game that finally gets me to genuinely like the series. The only real frustration I had was caused mostly by my own incompetence rather than bad game design, which is definitely good. It improves upon everything that made the previous two games unique and/or good, and for me at least, finally made the game enjoyable. Everything is better, the wildlife is a unique challenge at times, the story is interesting, and the game is just gorgeous.TL;DR Best game in the series so far, with few major flaws8/10Awesome"
