76561197987673438,Recommended,220240,8678332,"Posted: 12 January, 2014",all,Von Mäyrä,"Got to say Far Cry 3 is a brilliant package. Visually it's one of the most gorgeous games I've played so far. The tropical island is lush, appropriately has wild life here and there but not oversaturating the islands. Shooting and the hide and stabbing work satisfyingly well. Compared to Far Cry 2 the game has much more substance. There's much more to do in the open world and it doesn't feel so empty. Plus the driving, which actually in 3 is much more optional than in 2, has much more weight and is through that more enjoyable. There's a lot of good writing in characters, especially in the ""evil"" ones. But I suppose like with every open world game there comes the sense of repetition eventually. Focusing doing too many side quests and other side activities might make you a little bored after a while.I really didn't have any problems technically despite maybe a crash that happened once during the 18-hour playthrough but that's just really minor. If you've got the specs on your machine to run this game and you do enjoy a bit of open world FPS, can't say you're going wrong by buying and playing Far Cry 3. Unlike Far Cry 2 it's totally worth your time. It's a sweet piece of... smooth jungle beauty."
