,Recommended,220240,9114019,"Posted: 14 February, 2014",all,GrimReaper711,"What a mad adventure. This is definitely not your average shooter. As with the other games in the franchise, Far Cry 3 is an open-world RPG shooter. It follows the story of Jason Brody trying to save his friends from a group of pirates which have kidnapped them.The RPG apsect of things is great - it's not ""Put a point into a stat"" type stuff, but unlocking a skill tree which grants you the ability to do more things in the game. You also need to skin animals to create usefull items (which is a challenge in itself) and harvest plants to create various syringes which can be used to heal or provide temporary buffs.The game does feel a little ""grindy"" at parts, but this evens out the pace of the game and makes the story-driven sequences all the more enjoyable.Graphics 8/10  - Most of the game is apsoloutly gorgous. Motion capped voice actors make the animations look extremely fluid and realistic. Only loosing points due to a few low resolution textures here and there.AI 7/10  -  (I would say the AI is quite average)Gameplay 9/10  -  I think the gameplay promotes a stealth-like playthrough, but there is tons of room for people who like to run & gun their way through the game.Story 9/10  -  The story is interesting. There's going to be some things that people like, and some other things which people don't like.I highly reccemend this game."
