76561197993703405,Recommended,220240,11101627,"Posted: 6 July, 2014",all,UZI SUICIDE,"I'm glad I played Blood Dragon first, it helped with my strategy to know that it is important to spend time out early on in the game to craft bigger rucksacks and ammo holders, before the action gets too intense.  A lot of the money you will rely on is in the form of necklaces and trinkets, and you will get a full bag running around in the bush and end up dumping things you could otherwise sell.  Selling all this stuff is nice and easy thanks to the quicksell feature which lets you dump all the junk in one go, without needing to go line by line like dead island.  Also handy is the fill er up style ammo bulk buy, so you can run into a shop, sell all the crap, load up on guns, then get right back into it...Easy.The map is huge, theres load of dangerous animals and enemies to avoid or spread all over the beautiful landscape and the A.I. will kill you if you dont go in hard.  A game in the tradition of original FarCry, so beautiful and realistic you can almost smell the goats, and feel the tropical breeze.  I find myself holding my breath when diving under the oceans, this game draws you in.  Good story, well voice acted, and exciting action.  Regularly cheap on Steam sales, pick up the bundle with Blood Dragon and get ready for FC4 and BD2, out soon."
