r on becomes insane and likes killing, which I don't. He starts out saying, ""Oh ♥♥♥♥! He's dead!"" to, ""HE'S MOVING! BURN HIM, PUT ALL THE EXPLOSIVES ON HIM, MAKE SURE HE'S DEAAAAAAAD! RAAAAA BLOOOOOOOD!""-The endings. At the very end you have the left click option and the right click option. They both give seperate options. Nothing that happened before matters, just which button you click.-OH GOD NO! I'M REMEMBERING THE BOSS FIGHTS! GAAAAH. But seriously. The boss fights, which luckily there are only 3 of, are QTE's not including Vaas. Vaas is different, which I like.-How hard it was to come by money. I didn't do the sidequests during my campaign play, so it was super hard for me to get money, which I needed.-Uplay. 'Nuf said.So, in the end, was it worth the ten bucks getting the Far Cry Franchise Pack? Absolutely. Is it worth whatever it's priced at? Definitely. What would I rate it? 9/10. Yep. I liked it that much. BY THE WAY UPLAY NEEDS TO♥♥♥♥♥♥OFF!"
,Recommended,220240,15112290,"Posted: 29 March, 2015",all,Dubtack,"Price Aquired: $7:49 during Winter sale 2014I picked up this game after playing Far Cry 4 on the PS4. I was impressed with that game and wanted to see what else the series had to offer. I was very very surprised because in my opinion - Far Cry 3 blows Far Cry 4 out of the water. Since I've purchased Far Cry 3, I haven't played 4 at all because 3 just...feels better.The game does a great job of setting up the story in the opening, and I became invested in the characters very quickly. The main character, Jason Brody, is on a mission to rescue his captive friends after they became stranded on a jungle island following a skydiving accident. This is a really compelling mission, and I, as the player, felt really motivated to save them.I'm not good at starting and finishing Single-Player campaigns (the last one I finished was The Last Of Us Remastered over the summer), but I was hooked into this one from beginning to end.The gameplay is very fun and feels very responsive. Seeing how many guards you can silenty snipe before they alert the rest of the outpost is intense and rewards smart playing. There are plenty of customizable weapons and I always felt like I had options. There are many fun weapons as well (namely the Flamethrower).Gunfights are fun and feel fair. I was rarely frustrated (except for the damn heavy soldiers).Anyone who is worried about missing elephants and other improvements from FC4, don't be. I didn't miss them at all.The ONLY negative thing I have to say about this game is the occasional overuse of ""trippy"" drugs. The island natives occasionally give drugs to Jason to make him realize things from their perspective, and they lead to many many cool hallucination sequences. However they end up using this effect in a boss encounter or two and it takes away from the satisfaction of the fight. I would have preferred if they stuck to the realism a bit more in the boss sequences.I highly recommend this game if you like FPS games, games with a good storyline, or wanna see what the Far Cry franchise is all about for a good price."
,Recommended,220240,30733172,Posted: 25 March,all,Rale,"Pros:- Very long campaign (took me about 16 hours to complete)- Wide variety of weapons- Beatufiul graphics- Stealth works great in this game- Map is HUGE- The story for the campaign was very good- Campaign missions aren't repetitive- Game is optomized really well (it runs on my 2012 laptop with no dedicated graphics card and a core i5 @1.7ghz) at 40ish fps- You don't have to spend hours grinding to level up/ get cash/ get better itemsCons:- NoneThe only things I could wine about would be that you have to have Uplay to run the game (which is free to download and pretty easy to use), and that the achievements for the game are through Uplay instead of Steam.This game is beautiful. The graphics are amazing (even though I was playing on all low settings), I can't imagine what the game would look like on extra. The scenery in this game is so beautiful. Especially if you climb a radio tower, the view is just breath taking. The enemy AI in this game aren't stupid either, but they aren't too smart either. It was a pretty good balance. Also the map is very very big. It would probably take you around 15-20 minutes to get from one side of the map to the other on foot.If you're thinking about getting this game, you should. It's worth the money even if it's not on sale. I give it a 10/10."
