,Recommended,220240,8904483,"Posted: 29 January, 2014",all,Toxic League,"Far Cry 3 provides an epic story about a friendly vacation gone wrong. Jason Brody is your typical youngster who's only care is to party hard, but circumstance force him into a situation where this boy must jump on the fast path to manhood.The graphics of Far Cry 3 are simply stunning. This latest edition goes back to its original roots of lush island landscapes. The scenery is fantastic. As day changes to night and the rain starts pouring down, it provides a sense of realism that is rarely accomplished in many games today. Characters are amazingly detailed and the interaction with them add to that sense of realism. Vaas and Hoyt are two sick son of a ♥♥♥♥♥es that keep tensions high and continually throw unexpected twists your way. The different variety of vehicles like hang gliders, jet skis, and dune buggies make exploration fun, while sprinting is fast enough that it provides a reasonable alternative to using vehicles at all. The large variety of weapons allow for a full range of games styles, from stealth play to I'm here to blow♥♥♥♥♥♥up. I actually played very stealthily in the early parts of the game as the bow and arrow was probably hands down my favorite overall weapon, but later on I just overpowered my opponents with sheer firepower. I found both methods equally satisfying.Side missions are initially fun, but ultimately become repetitious after a while because they don't offer enough differences. Liberate enemy camps, expand your overall field of vision by claiming back radio towers, assassinate key figures, and hunt wild game. Hunting and skinning animals is necessary to upgrade your standard equipment. It goes well with the island paradise and doesn't heavily disrupt from the primary story.Three categories of character skills are available to promote stealth, firepower, and survival. Missions reward stealth gameplay with more XP which I don't necessarily agree with because it tends to steer your gameplay in that direction. I was able to unlock all available skills by the story's end. There's also crafting of drugs using flowers collected which can increase various attributes for a limited time.I found the menu system to be the weakest part of the game. It feels overly cumbersome since you have to escape out of the game to craft syringes or use skill points. It just doesn't feel like it was integrated well overall.All-in-all, Far Cry 3 represents a really fun open world first person shooter. Single player is genuinely fun, but I have yet to play the co-op or multiplayer elements."
