,Recommended,220240,9858590,"Posted: 18 April, 2014",all,Mi.Amas.Sienco,"Far Cry 3 definitely had some good things going for it, but it still was not without its faults.  Combat was fun, stealth play was done well enough for those that enjoy it, and I loved the open world.  Oh, and of course, the RPG elements were a welcome addition, even though choice is limited to unlock order and I reached the level cap well before the end of the game.  Unfortunately, enemy A.I. was mediocre, and when it came to stealth, enemies seemed either virturally blind or able to see through cover, depending on their type (pirates (red) v. privateers (yellow)).  Oh, and the boss fights kind of sucked.  My biggest complaint, however, would be that the game had a lot of filler content (Trials of the Rakyat, Tower Unlocks, Outpost Cleared, Supply Drops, Path of the Hunter Missions, Wanted Dead Missions, Letters Found, and Relics Found).  It was fun at first, but by about half way through, I was just doing that stuff to get the unlocks & experience (and because I'm kind of OCD about that kind of stuff).  It just started to get old by the time you've hunted down the 120th relic or did the 23rd Path of the Hunter.  I guess that's better than a short game or an empty world, but I would have like to have seen more variety with this content -well, assuming it was done well, of course; most of the side missions, were already rather forgettable.  Story missions, on the other hand, were varied and quite fun.Overall, I'd recommend the game, especially if you can pick it up for cheap during a sale.  Combat is satisfying, the story missions are fun, and unlocking new weapons and abilities changes things up and helps to make you feel like a badass.  The a.i. could have been better and the filler content gets a little old after a while, but then again, you can always do as little or as much as you like.  I also had a few other minor gripes (like the ease at which to take fall damage, crappy inventory system, many npc's looking the same, etcetera), but I don't think they detract enough from the game to warrant getting into.  7 out of 10 stars."
