,Recommended,220240,8035194,"Posted: 13 December, 2013",all,"Dr. Ted ""Crazy Legs"" Nelson","An engrossing open-world FPS, but not without its faults.  Beautiful graphics, intense gunfights, legitimately fun (if simple) stealth gameplay, and tons of content are the good parts. Like most open-world games, however, it becomes samey around the 20 hour mark and I started rushing story missions to get it done with. The not-so-good stuff: a) the storyline tends to pound on the ""You are just like the bad guys, GET IT?!"" theme in the dumbest ways possible; b) the people you are supposed to care about are aggressively stupid or bland, c) your character has the worst voice actor in the game, and d) the only memorable character (Vaas, who is plastered all over the marketing) is given relatively short shrift, but perhaps that's for the best - he's the best actor in the game and more exposure might have ruined his impact. That said, my gripes pertain mainly to the story missions (the majority of which are legitimately fun and/or exciting) and aren't enough to overcome its strengths; the game is definitely worth checking out and it's the best of the Far Cry games overall (I'm lying, Blood Dragon is the best)."
