,Recommended,220240,30291030,Posted: 2 March,all,indecendence,"Personal Rating: 5 of 10Its very difficult to review this game. The story and plot is good, the island is vast and combat is satisfying at times. However it falls really short on variety and many things don't gel together.Story is simple and straight foward but the plot did raise my eyebrows several times like the shocking kind which is good.The island is self is split into 2 part with the latter being revealed later in the game. The map is huge but I think mainly its because its empty and repetitive. The island looked the same everywhere with the same encampment, building, random places of small interest, mountain top and temples here and there but beyond that, the island is practically empty. For such a huge island there sure is no jungle. Don't expect different settings like snowy mountain, huge swampy area (there is a small and rather under designed one) or perhaps some remains of previous civilization. The reason I've said this is, there is proof of war bunkers, ancient temples and some large abandon facilities but these just isn't enough of other structures or towns to support it.Towns and encampments are plenty and scattered everywhere but they are really dead is coal. NPCs are decorations mostly that does nothing except for some that gives out quest. Not lively at all.Speaking of side quests, apart from collectibles, none of them span across a few series of repetitive quests like kill 250 of this and collect 50 of that but if you combine all of them together you get your fill series of repetitive nonsense lame side quests. Some side quests may obviously hide some meaning behind which others may find it funny or offensive but to me, I deemed them really unnecessary.Voice acting is alright but some NPCs voice record quality is clearly poor and bad also. Main characters are clearly stands out from unimportant NPCs as they are livelier and some are designed really well. Music is okay but it does gets on my nerve after a while because its so repetitive and some soundtrack clearly kills off the mood. Some main characters are overly done though which can be annoying. Thank heavens the interaction time with them isn't that long.The story mission is not really that long and the developers really hike up the challenge really really fast. Enemy A.I. is alright but once you find a flaw to exploit it seemingly easy. Weapons are plenty to choose from and yes they do have different characteristics which you can clearly feel but I feel they can be a little more hard hitting. You can customize weapons and even apply skin on them but its very limited. What surprises me the most is the animals. There is actually quite a few variety of them but lacked of characteristics.You can earn levels and money doing quests and looting but thats that. Collectibles unlocks written stories and provide nothing more. Each time, I was hoping the next collectible will unveil more location or puzzle but nothing really. Money allows you buy stuff. I was really excited at first but again dissapointed me as fast as it got me hyped up because you can only purchase weapons and customization. Ammos and med kit are practically useless as there are plenty around. Further more most of the weapons can be earned for free. Leveling up earns you a skill point and yeah the skills are quite useful nad gives you a sense of progression.You can also craft items in the game but personally I think it is a cheap gimmick. Imagine this, you needed leather to holster weapon. To carry more weapons you need more holster. But each holster requires different leather to craft. Its like her lets make use of the animals you know since its there but yeah its really redundant. You won't feel any sense of achievement there just finally I get more slots. You can also craft a variety of syringe that boosts/gives you certain ability for a short period of time. I only find 1 or 2 of them useful. In order to craft syringe you need to forage some plants. There are just too many of them lying around which practically makes them worthless.If you ever watched the trailer, it was really good. I thought that finally it went back to its root (Far Cry 1) but the actions you see in the trailer is more like in game ability kind of thing and not the actions you control of feel satisfy when you execute them. You only need to push a button at the right time. The antagonist that appeared on the trailer also sends shiver down one's spine. You hoped to see more of his insanity but no it doesn't really fills the expectation void. The character just don't expand.Overall, the game feels like it was designed by many department. Some did great while others pitched the idea, implement it for the sake of having the feature there in the game but these features don't simply cannot fit into the puzzle together and other aspects of the game cannot fully utilize one another to the fullest.Note that there are also some game breaking bugs too. Collecting collectibles doesn't save the game so if the game crashes (there are no quick save feature as I can't see the key mapping option), you need to repeat the process which is a pain. At times, if you land with the wingsuit you may clip through the ground. Missions contains plenty of unmarked checkpoint. If you somehow managed to bypass them you need to reload as the game won't progress.This game is good for casual open world game that packs some action. There are little things in the game that may surprise you or you may notice some small features that should be there."
