,Recommended,220240,8579986,"Posted: 5 January, 2014",all,pwnz0r3d,"Wow.What an absolute joy to play compared to the prequel, which was both tedious and bland. I never got around to finish Far Cry 2. This game I want to explore every little corner of, although I suspect that would take an enormous amount of time.The tropical island the game is set upon is huge. The missions and challenges seem endless. I recon playing through only the main storyline make the game shortlived, but then you're missing the point of the game entirely. Far Cry 3 is meant to be explored and behind every rock and palmtree, you always find something new worth exploring.Compared to the desert in Far Cry 2, the jungle (not surprisingly) feel much more alive. Birds and all kinds of animals inhabit all of the island, and they're not just hunting you. They're hunting each other too. At one point I came across a pack of hyenas hunting a flock of wild boars. Chasing after them with my sniper rifle, killing a couple of wild dogs in the process, a big tiger suddenly jumps one of the smaller predators. Superb.When you start the game, pirates have also set up countless of bases all around the island. They too seem aware of the surroundings, and after you liberate camps during the game for the islands natives, you will often meet the two factions in random encounters.The characters you follow in the main storyline are also great, the random and rich optional quests keeps the game fresh throughout, and the graphics are just beautiful to behold even on a lower spec computer like myself.The game runs almost flawless on PC, all the important options are present both for the novice and more advanced gamer. The only somewhat annoying problem I had, was that the game refused to stay in fullscreen between plays. Could have been my computer, but the borderless window-option in the menu eliminated the problem for me.Two things worth mentioning is that the game uses UPlay on top of Steam. I've had no issues with it, but it might put some buyers off. Also I have yet to try multiplayer in the game, which makes this review somewhat lacking.I got the game on one of the Steam-sales dirt cheap, but it's well worth the investment full price also. All in all a great, great game. Well done Ubisoft."
