,Recommended,220240,9498187,"Posted: 16 March, 2014",all,It's all so tiresome,"Far cry is a great first person free roaming game which is non-linear, meaning you can choose to do what you want within the game.  You can choose to hunt animals for skins to upgrade your equipment, hunt for collectibles, win races, conquer outposts controlled by pirates and so on.The actual story missions could be little less linear and more varied but it does the job. It has some memorable characters in it (Vaas, Bambi, Sam Becker, Hoyt)The co-op missions are a lot of fun, my problems with it is the public co-op, and the fact that you cannot choose the map you want to play unless you're the host, which doesn't happen often.  This leaves you to be slotted into a map which you might not want to play because you've played it too much or you would like get the achievement for completing another map.By the way, you do not get the acheivement for a map if you entered the map half way through a session - you must start from scratch. Another issue with entering a session midway through is you have to wait until the other players reach the next checkpoint to actually start playing which can take a long time on some maps and difficulties.This can all be avoided if you can organize private games using private co-op with your friends.Multi-player is the same old stuff really. It's not bad, but if you were honestly going to play a multiplayer fps, there are better ones out there.I came to this game from the position of never having played a game in this series before; so if you're in the same boat you wont be disappointed."
76561197970266696,Recommended,220240,9660221,"Posted: 29 March, 2014",all,Lou Cifer,"OK, so the single player is decent.  Good, even.  The action is fast-paced, you have many options for gameplay, from stealth to tank, the crafting is just engaging enough to keep you hunting and gathering materials, and the voice acting is tip-top.  The main problem is, boss battles that should be adrenaline-pumped shoot-em-ups end up being ridiculous QTE (that's Quick Time Events, for the blissfully unfamiliar), where you're following on-screen prompts to click/press buttons at the right times.  This is very disappointing, since the production quality has you pumped and ready for a battle royale.  However, it is not nearly as disappointing as coop and multiplayer.  The coop servers are down constantly.  Coop itself is buggy and glitchy, to this day.  The random bugs that permeate coop would, in my opinion, be unacceptable for launch day, let alone all this time later.  Yet they persist, and Ubi does nothing to rectify the problem.  I still have been unable to finish coop, because on those occassions I try to connect, the servers are often down, or buggy and not working.In summary, get this game on sale, and play single-player.  Pretend the boss fights were cool, and move on.  Probably the last Ubi title I buy.  Oh, and UPlay is required, and it is ridiculous."
