,Recommended,220240,5562005,"Posted: 24 February, 2013",all,Meeebil,"If you are and FPS fan, I strongly recommend getting this game. The graphics are great, it has well done stealth mechanics, and fun challenges to go through. And if you get bored of that (which you probably won't for a while), there is co-op to play. You can even create unique scenarios using the built in level editor, although it isn't well optimized for PC. The game also has a multiplayer mode, but it lacks creativity, and get old quickly.The singleplayer is immersive, with tons of replayability, an awesome story, and amazing characters. The characters help to make the already great story even livelier, especially the fun and creative villains, such as Vaas. You can also go collecting relics and selling the animal pelts that you collected. With card games, hunting, and much more, the Rook Islands never get old.The multiplayer isn't as well made as other FPS multiplayers, and definitely the weaker side of the game. It has a good bit of replay value with a level up feature, but again, you'll probably be spending more time on singleplayer.I personally give the game a strong 9/10."
