76561198067613074,Recommended,220240,8923272,"Posted: 31 January, 2014",all,wheel_of_whimsy,"Coming from recently playing Just Cause 2, I didn't expect the length of this campaign. Especially if you take the time to do side quests, DLC missions, and take over all the outposts and radio towers. This game is fantastic. You can run around and go in guns blazing, or you can sneak up and take everyone out quietly with silenced weapons or the bow. However, my favorite way to play is probably by getting to a high place and picking off enemies one by one with a sniper rifle. The campaign in this game is a must.The co-op is OK. It's not amazing, and I was disappointed that the co-op wasn't really open world like the single player campaign. You can play with up to four people, but you don't get all the abilities you have in the single player. One of the most fun parts of the co-op are the competitions. In each mission there is a part were all players are competing for the highest score. There are jet ski challenges, sniper challenges, bow challenges, RPG challenges, and more.The multiplayer was surprisingly fun. Most games like this that aren't built with a multiplayer focus are not very good. I find this one to be enjoyable. However, there are only a couple hundred people who play regularly, so you cannot play most game modes.There are some things in this game that just make you go ""What?"" Because as realistic as it seems most of the time, sometimes there are just crazy things. I won't tell you any so it's not spoiled, but be prepared for some crazy stuff."
