,Recommended,220240,1904397,"Posted: 8 January, 2013",all,Cr4zy,"FarCry 3 is a game I wanted to like, every review said it's awesome. So naturally I bought into the hype, normally a single player game either bores me in an hour or two or gets completed in 4-5hours.FC3 is different, because I want to play the whole damn thing again and the first time took 22hours. It actually is as amazing as reviewers say. It has a nice flow to the story, and you aren't forced into mission after mission, pick them up when you want, have a break, go hunt a bear, regret that decision, but at least you now have a bigger loot bag, or can hold more weapons.The tiny little interactions, the massive islands to explore and the constant want for more kept me coming back. If one thing bores you, go and try something else in another part, liberate a camp, hunt a croc with a machete.Along with the fact it's actually a PC game. The visuals are stunning, sure you need a PC to power them, but what would a PC game be if it didn't push hardware. The options to change things like FOV are sorely missed in many games and it's refreshing to see someone, especially Ubisoft, make things right.TL:DR Farcry 3 is a solid single player experience, with hours upon hours of story and side missions, giving you a choice on how you play the game. Add in the stunning scenery and gorgeous art you will keep coming back for more."
