,Recommended,220240,10588112,"Posted: 20 June, 2014",all,Some old gamer,"I've played this game for over 100 hours... and I still love playing it.  I rate the game a 9/10 because no game is perfect but this one is close.Surviving the jungle is the first challenge for Jason Brody.  The jungle will kill you if you don't watch out for the wild animals.  If surviving the jungle isn't tough enough for you, you're in luck.  The roads are just as dangerous as the jungle early on.  Pirates patroll the roads with .30 and .50 caliber machine guns mounted on top of Jeeps or just 2-4 guys with AK-47's in the back of a truck.  Once Jason completes a few missions, crafts a few bags and holsters and unlocks a few parts of the tattoo the game really takes off.  Jason goes from a scared early 20 something kid to a merciless pirate killing machine quickly. Whatever you do, don't shoot innocent people, you get punished for it in game.  The Islands are huge and the South Island is much more challenging than the North Island.  On the South Island, you trade Pirates for a trained and well armed private army.Good Job Ubisoft, this is currently my favorite action FPS of all time."
