76561198000710694,Recommended,220240,8173689,"Posted: 21 December, 2013",all,Coquine Mouillée,"Far Cry 3 is probably one of the best FPS's I've played in a long time. The gameplay is simply amazing, featuring some of the most fun and satisfying stealth mechanics I've seen coupled with a very solid selection of weapons and a great variety of missions. The game looks great, the tropical equivalent of Skyrim : walking in the jungle grass slowly, swimming silently towards a group of unsuspecting bandits or climbing atop a huge, rocky cliff never looked so good. You'll feel like Indiana Jones or Robinson Crusoe, fighting against the elements, hunting dangerous animals or exploring ancient tombs. The gunfights are fast-paced and rightfully chaotic, the enemies' reactions are realistic (although it's hard not to miss some things the AI did in Far Cry 2, like soldiers trying to save their wounded allies) and the game world is tons of fun to explore and conquer.The story is the only element, in my opinion, that truly lacks polishing. Through the whole single player mode, you feel like the writers at Ubisoft tried to set up something about insanity, about the villain, Vaas, about a lot of interesting elements that they end up litterally ignoring or throwing away about halfway through. It is extremely frustrating : it's a poorly told story, yet you constantly feel like it could've actually been good if only a few elements had been changed or added. It feels like it could've been good, which is even more annoying that something that's irredeemable. The story barely makes any sense, you can't help but hate its protagonist and the game's ending feels rushed. As usual, Ubisoft is great at introducing great ideas before depriving them of all their potential, just like they made Assassin's Creed uninteresting by adding the whole storyline about the Animus and Desmond instead of focusing on the actual assassins that everyone wanted more of.Even as a gamer that wants a good story, though, I can still recommend Far Cry 3 to just about anyone because the gameplay simply feels amazing. Any fan of FPS will love this game, especially if you're a fan of stealth mechanics. I've played through this game twice, which is something I don't do often, because Far Cry 3 offers a fantastic game world in which you can truly feel like a lone predator of the wild, an action movie hero."
