,Recommended,220240,14766768,"Posted: 6 March, 2015",all,Ravenize > *,"I was huge fan of the original Far Cry, but when the developer switched I followed CryTek to Crysis instead of continuing the series. I played Far Cry 2 yeras late and didn't enjoy it. It was so different from what I expected given the original that I couldn't be anything but disappointed.Far Cry 3 nails the formula though. What they tried to do with 2 in regards to the open world and quests and forts that need to be taken over finally evolved into something fun and engaging. I found myself trying to do everything possible in Far Cry 3. All the side activities, like activating radar towers or racing on a supply drop are just fun. They're all different enough to make exploring and completing these quests as you find them a worthy goal in its own. And the light RPG elements with the skill tree added an extra layer of depth sorely needed to the FPS genre.On top of that, I also really liked the story, which was another complaint of mine about 2. I'm really happy that they were able to create something interesting and compelling to move the action along, from the first moment to the last. Some of the trippy scenes are incredibly original and they make for a really memerable experience.The final bonus from this game is casting Michael Mando as Vaas. He gives an incredible performance as one my favorite villians in recent memory."
