76561198048091979,Recommended,220240,8079036,"Posted: 17 December, 2013",all,Prometheus Unbound,"Not for the faint hearted or those who prefer to just run into situations guns blazing.This game is a thinking persons game. You need to plan your tactics before entering most situations. Enemies are, mostly, smart and will not stand there for you to shoot them when you are in combat. Add to this an array of weapons big and small that would have John Rambo as excited as a kid in a candy store, an RPG like element which teaches you certain skills for various situations, a stealth system that actually works, and combat that never fails to get your heart pumping, you have a mix of elements that will have you getting really involved in the world.Tactics: You really need to plan your actions in this game. The health system is kind enough to give you a certain amount of survivability, but get caught in the middle of 10 enemies all packing big guns, and you are gonna hit the dirt faster than you can get more than a clip of shots off (and that is on easy mode). This game makes you think, and gives you options for how you take on enemies.Enemies: These guys have their flaws. But mostly they are smart enough to run for cover, aim properly, and use tactics of their own such as attempting to flank you. They tend to hunt you relentlesly if you run away, and will only give up after you have run a certain distance.Weapons: This game gives you an array of weapons that are quite extensive and suited to any tactics you want to use. Most of them come with modifications that will enhance their usefulness. Some weapons become free as you advance in the game.RPG Elements: This is kept somewhat thematic by the fact you are not a trained merc or anything like that. You are a civilian. So you need to learn combat abilities as you go. It uses the idea of you being initiated into the islands tribal warrior class using tattoos that mark your advancement in various areas of combat techniques. This element strongly has you thinking of the way you want to take on your enemies from the first time you get to choose an ability.Stealth: This relies on, mainly, cover. Cover includes the obvious, such as walls, structures, and vehicles. But it also expands to things such as trees, bushes and the like. There are a few stealth based weapons available, meaning that you can really use stealth to your advantage. And There are abilities which allow you to perform stealth takedowns.Combat: Fast paced, explosive and violent. Combat is very well implemented. Even when in combat with small groups of enemies. You will find your adrenaline pumping and your brain working overtime.All these elements need to be experienced to get an understanding of how good they make this game. If you want a game that makes you feel Rambo or Mclain style. This is for you.10/10"
,Recommended,220240,13573175,"Posted: 24 December, 2014",all,Poser Punx,"Oh Far Cry 3....How I enjoyed thee......It has a great atmosphere. Beautiful graphics ( in my opinion, close to todays standards )....One of the things that I did not like, was how fast the storyline went. I have 20+ hours of gameplay and at least 10-15 hours of it is exploration I decided to do ( Find outposts, towers, ect.. ). Things that, I highly recommend you do. However, if you enjoy a challenge, only do them based off the games storyline.I took most of the time to upgrade all gear and find all the posts/tower before doing anything. I, however, found that the game became EXTREMELY easy afterwards. So, it really depends on how you wish to enjoy it. That's the other thing I really enjoyed about FC3, it allows you to play at your own pace, heck, even during quests there are only really a handful of missions that are ""time-based"" ( and if you gear up like I did, it will become -too- easy to complete these timed challenges ).I highly recommend everyone to give this game a whirl. Especially if you're contemplating on getting Far Cry 4, it allows you to experience the Far Cry franchise ( if you haven't yet ) before spending $50+ on a new release.9/10- Poser Punx"
