76561198098798394,Recommended,220240,9888095,"Posted: 20 April, 2014",all,Glacious,"""Skyrim with Guns"" they call it. And how freaking right they are! With this being released just at the end of the year 2012 it easily makes for one of the best games of the year. Having played only Far Cry 2 in the past and having somewhat enjoyed some elements of the game but never actually got round to finishing it, I was in for a ride with Far Cry 3. The main selling point for me to picking up this title was Vaas. Plain and Simple. I loved Michael Mando's role as Vaas, It was absolutely fantastic! When I saw the Character Vaas, I knew this was a game I had to get in on despite my lack of interest from the previous Far Cry games. I absolutely loved every encounter with Vaas and easily one my favorite Antagonist's to date!Let's crack in with the detail. You play as Jason Brody. You, Your Brothers and some Friends go on a vacation in Bangkok as celebration of your Brother Riley as he obtained his Pilot License. Celebration is cut short after a Skydiving trip after having land upon a Pirate Island. You and your group get captured by the Pirate Lord known as Vaas, a Secondary Antagonist to this story. Shortly after your escape, you are aware of what goes on within the Huge open world known as Rook Islands. Slavery. Your friends have been taken captive and only you can save them against Tyranny of Slavery. You must adapt to your new surroundings or be consumed by them.How open world is Rook Islands you may ask? VERY open! The map is huge! Tons of exploration as you wonder through the Island discovering Historic Relics, gazing at Ancient tombs, Shrines and even weapons! Rook Islands is certainly a stunning place to be. With the vast amounts of exploration you will want to be doing deep in the Jungle you are going to be wanting to get around as running simply isnt fast enough to get from point A to B. There are various ways to get around Rook Island. Ground Vechiles consist of Jeeps, Quad Bikes and even Dune Buggies! With Aquatic transportation simply boats or Jet Ski's to get around, though preferably boats. Specially if your hunting a certain predator out in those waters...And last but not least is Air, no not Helicopters or planes but Hang Gliders! What a way to get from Point A to B... Glide to your destination and enjoy the sight bestowed upon you! Ubisoft truly went to town with the detail in Far Cry 3's enviroment and certainly wanted us to enjoy it, with the time spent in the Jungle hunting or in the air gliding across the Island, its hard not to appreciate Rook Islands Beauty and Ubisoft's hard work.Throughout your journey ahead you will require upgrades to make Jason a more efficient Warrior. This is where the Hunting kicks into play. While exploring the Jungle you will be sure to discover plenty of wild animals that you can kill and skin so you can craft new equipment such Weapon Holsters, Increased Lootpacks, Syringe Pouches etc. A very nice feature and certinaly one I enjoyed. Prowling through the jungle with my Sniper Rifle taking out wild beasts before being bested by a Tiger. Dang! Be aware of your surroundings, The hunter is also the Hunted.While exploring the Jungle you will come across Plants you can harvest for which you can make Syringes with to enhance Jason.  Syringes of the likes of Fireproof and the Ability to see Enemies through walls. Given that they are a timed effect but still useful. I havent crafted them all however the more creativity you have with Far Cry 3, the much better experience you will have.Throughout the game as you hunt, complete missions, discover viewpoints (Towers that expand the view of your map, similar to those of seen in AC series) you will earn Experience. The experience will reward you Skill points in which you can use to unlock new talents in three categories. The Heron, Shark and Spider. You are not devoted to one category, you can spend your points across all three Specializations. As you begin to build up your new found traits you will begin to build up whats called ""Tatau"". Symbolized on your Left arm, this Tattoo represents a Warrior from the Rakyat tribe in which you aid against Vaas and his Pirates. As you progress through the game and spend more well earned skill points, the tattoo will begin to expand along your arm.With alot of the single player aspects, what else is there to do other than explore and discover the collectibles of Rook Island? Far Cry 3 also packs in a multiplayer to boot, personally I have no interest in the multiplayer as I'm interested in the Single player mainly however it may be something to be explored in time of writing of this review however nice to see they had time to implement this in along side their Epic campaign. However it doesnt stop there! Oh no! They went even further and added a Co-op Story mode, seperate to the story of single player mode might I add! The story of the Co-op mode is set a few months prior to the story of the single player campaign and revolves around four characters, scammed out of their money by the pirates and they won't rest easy about it! Again having not played this side just yet, its still nice to see another addition to the package! More content!!!Having spent 25hours to finish the Single Player Campaign alone while doing some hunting, side objectives and sightseeing I still have yet much to accompish. Discovering all the relics, completing the rest of the side missions and fully upgrading my arsenal whether it be my weapons or simply hunting related gear. Theres still much left after your done in Far Cry 3 and then if your curious enough to try out the multiplayer or Co-op mode that will earn you even more hours upon your gametime. Far Cry 3 is worth your time and money! I would give this game a 9/10. A must buy, The single player alone was worth it for me but yet much more to be done with this title!"
