,Recommended,220240,21788236,"Posted: 12 March, 2016",all,anull,"This is a traumatic, exhilarating first person experience.You will brutally murder people with a machete, tear the skin off of wild animals while they're still warm, dig countless bullets out of your body with a knife and crash Jeeps into ancient underground ruins. You will be mauled by sharks, crocodiles, bears and dingos, get maimed and imprisoned multiple times by a lunatic, accidentally trip some serious balls on hallucinogenic shrooms in a cave, and that's just the first hour of the game.The tropical island that you'll be annihilating with an increasingly powerful arsenal of weaponry also happens to be inhabited purely by idiots and psychopaths. There is not one single pleasant human being to interact with, and everything that anyone says seems like it was hastily written on the back of a Mountain Dew wrapper in between crunch time coding sessions by young interns.You end up as a severely disturbed dweeb♥♥♥♥♥Rambo who realises that the inconceivable genocide he ends up having committed for the benefit of the ingrate, cretinous indigenous folk has irreversibly sent his sanity down the crapper. The constant intravenous intake of strong narcotics to dull the staggering physical ordeals hasn't helped either. He concedes that he can no longer integrate with human society and must therefore remain far removed from it, much to the complete indifference of his phony, sociopath ""friends"" he risked life and limb for again and again.It's a tragic tale, flimsily executed and aspiring to be more than it is, clumsily told and lacking any profound meaning or satisfying conclusion, with plot holes as large as undead bears. But who needs a relatable, engaging narrative when you'll be living vicariously through white 20-something middle-class male juvenile power fantasies blowing up stuff real good and sniping Machiavellian bad guys in the face, all in a gorgeously rendered setting with superbly smooth, crisp controls?100% still worth playing in 2016."
,Recommended,220240,7859330,"Posted: 1 December, 2013",all,Plymouth Harrison,"So let me give my overall opinion of this game, and work backwards; It's good. A fun FPS with a fairly decent story and good characters. However, it's by no means perfect. I have a lot of problems with the game that range from glitches, the combat, the story it self, and controls.-StorySo we enter the shoes of a kid named Jason Brody, a young man who loves living life to the extreme, though things like Sky diving, mountain climbing and surfing. He, his brothers and friends are within the ranks of the biggest stuck-ups in the universe, being incredibly rich to the point of irritation, and being♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥to the residents of their first vacation spot. However things quickly change when they are told by a DC to go to Rook Island, presumably thinking that there were no rules there.When they arrive, they are quickly apprehended by a group of pirates lead by Vaas Montenegro. However Jason manages to escape and is picked up by local tribe that quickly assimilates him into their ranks of Warriors, thanks to Citra. He does so with a porous, to save his friends and go home. Though out the game, a Dr. Earnheart watches over the friends of Jason while he goes off to save them.But nothing is this simple on Rook. Thoughout the course of the story, he slowly goes mad, enjoying the killing, the drugs, the guns. It leads up to him having to make a choice as to weather or not to stay or leave Rook.I wont explain much else, otherwise spoiling it.Overall, good story. Rather dumb, channeling Rambo for better or worse, but good.-Gameplay and MechanicsI'll go though this from disliked to liked.First off, who the hell thought it was a good idea to bind the Grenade key to the middle mouse button? Or switch grenades to rolling the mouse wheel? Same thing with the drugs, binded to keys I don't use that often, being way the hell out on 7 and 8. Whatever, I managed to rebind them and move on. No big deal, just a personal bug-bear of mine.Melee-play. ughhhh....UGGHHHHH *goes to throw self off a tower* It's so ♥♥♥♥ing boring. You push one button to do a quick slash with a machete, it's unfun and a major missed opportunity.Loot. There is no point to loot in this game, you don't find any interesting weapons, and you can only flog the lot when you get it for money. The colorful dialogue for the stuff is pointless. It would be cool if there was a model of whatever the item is, but there isn't.Hunting. What a great idea in this game, but wow did it miss some opportunities. After you craft all the items though hunting, there is no point to keep hunting, because you don't eat, don't need new clothing, don't need anything like that. After you get everything, it's down to the shop to flog the lot. I wish there was a better way to go about it, but there isn't, it's just dumb.The drugs. Right, I tired them just to say ""Hey I tried em'"" but was not impressed at all. I was expecting to see some trippy♥♥♥♥♥state and beable to see the enemies from the point of view of a bird or something. Instead it just looked like the Sniper ran though smashing Jarate on everyone's heads, and was unimpressed. So while it was toted really well, it was just a boring little gimmick in my mind, and I never used them.The missions them selves were ♥♥♥♥in' sweet for the most part. Everyone who's played it will know of the Burning Weed level. That♥♥♥♥♥♥was awesome. However, with some missions, you get this sense of it's trying to funnel you from one area to the next. All of them contribe a reason for you to be in a valley of some descriptions, or stuck on a low lying island, or asked to stay in one position and snipe. It's irritating, although the missions are still put together really well. Nothing is over done, or underdone, it's just right.Driving. Yeah it's all right, coming from a background of racers, the driving is by no means bad and it's nice to drive a sodding truck for once.The radio towers were defiantly one of the better fetures, but it raised two questions in my mind;1. How can a radio tower have an effect on a GPS when GPS Units don't use the towers?2. Why the ♥♥♥♥ can't I get a paper map that has everything on it?So to 'unlock' parts of the map on GPS, you need to climb up these towers that are scattered all over the island and activate them (?). It's interesting, but with the two questions above it does kind of prove moot. But I do like it, as the towers are varied in the states of decay they lie in, and it makes for a challenge at points to climb the towers.Gun-play and customization. I suspect this is where a bulk of the budget went, as the guns, while limited are fairly fun to use and sound ♥♥♥♥ing awesome. Except for the .357 and Desert Eagle, I mean Jesus ♥♥♥♥ing Christ. The weapons are all fun to use, and can be used at any point. You don't need to upgrade to a more powerful weapon to fight with, you can just use what you like. That's fairly cool. The customization is really nice, albeit limited. You can give the guns paint jobs and upgrades that add scopes, silencers and extended magazines. Again, multiple misfires here. More items to put on the guns, or a painter to make your own design would of been awesome, but someone failed to bring this up. Explosions are particularly epic, so is using fire to suppress the enemy.Stealth. This is easily my favorite aspect, as it sheds away everything from the ♥♥♥♥♥♥ economy, the broken loot and hunting system and uses the game's great gun-play and ideas to it's benefit. It's so satisfying to beable to sneak into a base and kill everyone without alerting anyone. Or if you♥♥♥♥♥♥it up, you can still go run and hide before reinforcements show up, then kill them off that way. One problem; The AI is brain dead, and if they can't find you, they go back to their patrols as if nothing happened, even walking across the body. That's forgivable, if a little annoying. Example; I got a stealth kill with a big ♥♥♥♥ off truck, and the guard's friend said ""It must've been my imagination"" ignoring the now burning truck that slammed into a pole.Overall the gameplay is good, but man does it miss the target in areas. Definably worth playing, if only for the gun-play and stealth.-Ghrapics and PerformanceThis game is beautiful. I love how everything looks, that even though the situation it self is ♥♥♥♥♥♥, it takes place in such a pretty locale that it easies the trauma of the situation. My computer handled it really well, even when things got busy, the frame rate never dropped bellow 30, and remained at a consistent 45-50 FPS at all other times.It's pretty and runs well. Derp.-OverallIt's a good game, with some neat ideas, good mechanics, pretty environment, well made characters (if a derpy♥♥♥♥♥story), and a fun stealth element. I recommend it, but just bare in mind, it's really, really basic. There is nothing here that hasn't been done before or better. I recommend it only for the stealth, story and gunplay. Other then that, blehhhh."
