76561198216663797,Recommended,220240,25070386,"Posted: 22 August, 2016",all,Bubblejuiceman,"As far as this game goes, it's gameplay is fantastic, and the story concept is great. If you haven't played this yet, you absolutely need to. This is a can't miss open world fps, from the graphics, to the smooth and satisfying gunplay.However, I will next vent my opinion on the ending. If you read it, please understand that my feelings about the ending do not change the fact that I love this game and think everyone should have a playthrough.Just my opinion here, after being thoroughly disappointed by the ending:""Save Friends"" ending should have at least had a cut scene where you talk to your friends before they leave, and at least say goodbye. It felt empty and unsatisfactory that Citra dies, your friends leave without a word, Dennis disappears (it seems) and you're just... done?""Join Citra"" ending was pretty stupid to me, maybe if there was a trippy cut scene showing your future kid being a ruler, or maybe explaining why the hell you had to die, it might be more worth while (kind of).Either way, both ending were left without explanation, and it was rather disappointing. The gameplay itself is amazing, and the story was alright until the ending.If the devs didn't want to put more effort into a cut scene, they could have at least left a optional conversation with Dennis back at the temple or Amanaki village.Good ending: Jason explains his decision and what he said to his friends, brother, and girlfriend. (Those are pretty deep relationships to just cut off without a conversation).Bad ending: Dennis explains why Citra stabs you while spouting nonsense, and what the means for the village. (They'd have to get creative as to why you're still alive to free roam the island after you've been stabbed).P.S. I understand that the free roam after the game isn't considered a continuation to Jason ""after"" the story ends, because if you chose the bad ending, then how could he free roa