,Recommended,220240,15554472,"Posted: 26 April, 2015",all,ADD ME FOR GWENT,"FarCry 3 is a well rounded action-adventure title which provides many approaches as you explore its open world. For example, when you attempt to raid a pirate camp, you could:1) Sneak in and disable the alarm, followed by taking down each enemy with a meelee strike from his blindside(the game kind of promotes this approach with multiple take down bonuses and skills)2) Charge in and kill everyone before the alarm for reinforcements is sounded3) Charge in and kill everyone, and then kill all the reinforcements4) Snipe away (alarm systems, animal cages, pirates) with an upgraded sniper rifle or bowMy favorite is the last option, but most of the time I would screw up and would have to find new hiding spots, or to charge in and finish off the remaining pirates. I got to do pretty much everything and I enjoyed it.While claiming objectives like pirates camps and radio towers are not compulsory, doing so unlocks fast travel locations that can help you get from places to places for the campaign. The story has a nice flow, and you get to know and work with various characters in getting information, sabotaging the pirate network, saving your captured friends etc. Although halfway through you are forced to work for an a$shole and go into tombs in search of an ancient artifact (hello, Tomb Raider rip off?). I really didn't enjoy that portion, and they weren't short quests either.There were some other minor things I didn't like too. For example, what the hell is with the cut scenes of Alice quotes and♥♥♥♥♥♥ I thought they were completely random and unnecessary. Some people might also have issues with Uplay, as you have to create an account to play the game, even though you bought it via Steam. While I didn't have issues with Uplay not running, it wasn't nice having to wait for the program to start up and sync god-knows-what before the game actually runs. Also, note that there are no Steam achievements but Uplay ones instead, so ayy lmao who cARES xDDThere are numerous transport options from rovers and buggies to gliders and parachutes to speedboats. There are also numerous weapons, each with different upgrades and skins. While traveling, you encounter a variety of wildlife and I spent quite some time hunting to upgrade my equipment.I really liked the gameplay Far Cry 3 provides.9.5/10"
