76561198028352716,Recommended,220240,7875962,"Posted: 1 December, 2013",all,Ashley Schaeffer,"This is the single player FPS FarCry experience I was waiting for and UbiSoft finally delivered!THE STORY:I’ll be honest, the story is extremely forgettable… but the overall freedom to explore the island FPS style totally makes up for it.OPEN WORLD/DANGER:I loved the open world (island) and how much freedom you had to go explore it on a whim with all its thrills and danger. Take to the land with ATV’s, Dune Buggy’s, Cars or to the sea in Boats and Jet Ski’s or to the sky with Hang Glider's or a Wing Suit!I spent more time exploring the island, hunting animals/collectables and playing poker and the knife throwing game with the local NPC’s than I probably did with the main part of the game.The addition of wild animals really added to the life of the island and something that FarCry2 was severely lacking. There is finally a sense of danger in FarCry3 from the environment and what lurks within it. Panthers, Tigers, Bears, Hounds, Komodo Dragons, Snakes, Crocodiles, Sharks… and that’s not even including the varied human enemies.COMBAT:Oh baby this was fun and probably one of the best FPS single player combat systems I have ever played, so many memorable moments.Nothing like strapping C4 to a hang glider, using said glider to fly into an enemy base, bail from the hang glider near ground level, watch the hang glider finish swooping into the base and then me hitting the detonate button as I began my all-out attack as the flames from the crash began to spread all over the base.OrSneaking into an enemy base with only a bow and arrow and strategically picking off enemies one by one on the perimeter before making my way inside and doing some stealthily CQC kills with the combat knife.OrThe time I was able to shoot the bamboo cage where a Tiger was being held captive only to free it and watch it go on a ravenous rampage of revenge, providing me with the perfect distraction to let it rip with my machine gun.The weapons felt true to their real world counterparts and all the options you had to play the game your way how you wanted was at times blissfully excessive. I loved it.MY VERDICT:Based purely on the single player aspect of the game and it's complete freedom to explore, craft, hunt, play mini-games, etc. as far as FPS go I would give it a solid 4.5 out of 5."
