76561197994954550,Recommended,220240,27526236,"Posted: 25 November, 2016",all,Black Rock,Cooll
,Recommended,220240,16957751,"Posted: 9 July, 2015",all,DimeTree,"Far Cry 3: My Favorite Game Ever (Maybe)Far Cry 3 is an open world first person shooter with some RPG and Stealth elements. But there's so much more to it than that. Being a very cynical and critical person that, despite being an avid ""gamer"" pretty much my whole life, doesn't like video games that much, I'm shocked to say that this game is a valid contender to my favorite game ever. This does not mean I consider it the best game ever, I mean that out of every game in my life I've ever played, this is what I might have gotten the most enjoyment and fun out of. The game that I've liked the most. Now, without further ado, my full, unbiased assessment of the game.Gameplay: Loads of Shooty Sneaky FunThe gameplay consists of exploration, combat and side activities. In Far Cry 3, you explore a large, colorful and lively island called ""Rook Island"", filled with settlements, caves, small islands, mountains, lakes, and so much more. There are plenty of collectibles and loot out there waiting to be found, as well as lots of other cool secrets and easter eggs I won't spoil. You can get around by foot, car, boat, hanglider and even awingsuitlater in the game.The combat has you fighting both humans and animals that you find around the island. There are mainly two ways of dealing with threats: The shooty explody messy loud way using firearms, grenades and other fun stuff, and the sneaky stealthy stabby way, using your knife, rocks to distract enemies, and other stuff. Both are fun and have their advantages and disadvantages. I did, though, find stealth as the way to go in most cases, since you die quickly in firefights since Jason isn't a superhero that can just shrug off bullets by biting them out of- oh, wait, nevermind.The game has a diverse selection of weapons, in the categories as what you would expect (Assault Rifle, pistol, machine gun, sniper rifle, grenade launcher, shotgun, etc.), but also has some more unique items if you're not a whiny ♥♥♥♥♥ (Recurve bow with explosive arrows, flare gun, a mother♥♥♥♥ing flamethrower, etc.).If you're like most people, you'll try to stealth it up most of the time, but inevitably slip up, get caught, go rambo style and blow everything up.Story: A Tale of Friendship, Truth and Lots and Lots of DrugsThe story might just be one of the best parts of this game. I'm not going to spoil too much of it, but I'll give the basic outline.You are Jason Brody, an annoying rich spoiled white kid who has come to an island with his friends, who are also rich white kids. Before long they are all captured by pirates, and Jason ends up in the camp of Vaas. the insane main antagonist of the game. He manages to barely escape, where upon he is rescued by the Rakyat, a tribe fighting the pirates and struggling to regain freedom. You become a beacon of hope for their movement, being the only person to ever escape Vaas's camp alive. Throughout the game you will help their movement, adapt to your new environment and attempt to rescue your friends. But the journey will change you drastically, for better or worse.The game features a large cast of diverse, believable characters, the voice acting is superb, and the story is overall absorbing and very well written, with some of the most fantastic dialogue I've ever seen in a video game.Conclusion9/10. Has some very minor flaws, but overall a nearly perfect game."
76561197986515995,Recommended,220240,17124934,"Posted: 19 July, 2015",all,D3s_ToD3s,"A typical combat mission involves scouting the area from a vantage point, marking targets, picking the optimal angle of approach, and taking down the baddies one by one. It’s quite relaxing really, like pruning a rosebush where the roses can get freaked out and call another rosebush to come and back it up. And it’s always very satisfying to pull it off without being spotted, although the nature of an organic sandbox can lead to some odd results.One time I was carefully scouting an enemy base and just about decided on the best angle of attack when a ♥♥♥♥ing tiger lolloped into the base and ♥♥♥♥ing cleared it out with strategic maulings. What a right wally Mister ♥♥♥♥♥cat has made me look like, but it’s the sort of thing that’d never ♥♥♥♥ing happen in Call of Duty, isn’t it? Not unless Mister ♥♥♥♥♥cat was a programmed setpiece with ties to Al Qaeda.Ben ""Yahtzee"" Croshaw - December 2012"
