,Recommended,220240,11471167,"Posted: 29 July, 2014",all,SirGringo128,"I have been playing far cry 3 for quite some time. As you can see I have put over 200 hours into this game, and I still haven't come close to finishing everything there is to offer. I would like to break my reviews into catagorys. So here we go.Story:Far Cry 3 has you playing as a guy named Jason, and you and your friends are out partying cause your brother Riley just got his pilot lincese. You guys eventually end up going sky diving and landing on the island of Rook. Only to get captured by pirates. Wonderful right I know. Well you end up with your brother Grant a soldier in some prison ruin by the pirates and being tormented by Vaas. This crazy sob who you will have to deal with several occations throughout the game. Then some certain events happen and you are ruining for your life all by yourself in the jungle. You end up falling into a river. Which after this leads you on a quest threw temples, mountains, caves, drug addicts, and the freaking CIA. I would give the story for far cry 3 a 9/10Gameplay:The gameplay that this game has is ridiculously bad♥♥♥♥♥ You start off with literally nothing, and as you progress you can craft items to store more ammo, guns, grenades, etc. You may be asking how do I craft these items. Well you will have to hunts animals. There is a wide varity of animals in this game from the common chicken all the way down to black panthers. The movements in this game are simple and fast paced. Which I really enjoy. There are some slow momments, but they lead to these epic intense gunfights. There is also a cool skill tree. That you can build up by leveling up your character. Then you have outpost you can capture and a bunch of side quest. You will be playing this game for a long time. I give the gameplay a 10/10Graphics:The graphics are beautfiful. There will be moments where you will  stop just to look at waterfall, volcano, etc., and see how beautiful the envoriment is. The island of Rook would be an awesome place to go on vacation. If it weren't infested with some many pirates and deadly animals. I give the graphics an 8/10.Cons:There really aren't to many. I mean a few glitches here and there, but its extremely rare. Some frame drop, but it isn't noticeable. Also it's run through uplay. Which means crashes because Uplay freakin sucks.All in all far cry 3 is a well designed, fun game. I would reccomend this if your a fan of fps or you just like to start up chaos. My finally rating of this game is a 9.8/10."
