,Recommended,220240,8002631,"Posted: 11 December, 2013",all,Blubbermaggot,"Far Cry 3 is a decent enough game. It has its flaws, such as an unlikeable and unrelateable protagonist. It's supposedly set on an island in the Pacific, but instead of having its own identity, it feels more like a mash-up of touring a pirate/mercenary-ridden Hawaii with New Zealanders, South Africans and Australians.The combat is well done and the main characters are memorable. The level-up system works well too. The voice acting is good but some NPC's get annoying after a while. I played in 1920×1080 and the graphics looked fine; I only had one instance of a graphic bug in 35+ hours of play.One game play issue with using a game pad (I used X360) was the ""hold X to do something"" such as loot body, swap weapon, enter vehicle or enter door; all mapped to the same button -  which became frustrating during moments when I couldn't stop to see which option ""hold X"" would do.To me, tap X to loot or enter door, hold X to swap weapon or enter vehicle and remap reload to something like tap Y, and then hold Y to heal would have been better.Overall an enjoying experience.Requires Ubisoft's Uplay too so be prepared to deal with that."
