76561198045208825,Recommended,220240,10790559,"Posted: 25 June, 2014",all,Shatiz,"***Get it cheap and play for gameplay, not the story. Kill pirates and be happy***You play as Jason, a member of a pack of spoiled rich kids trapped on an island after parachuting down to it only to be captured by pirates. The game is mainly killing said pirates, saving your friends and trying to get off the island.Shooting pirates is defintely the most... and pretty much only really fun thing in the game. Sneaking up on an encampment and trying to sneakily kill of the pirates without being seen is fun. The stealth mechanic works well (although sometimes enemies can see corpses that they should not be able to see). Overall the enemy AI is pretty good and the guns handle well.Unfortunately you are doing it in a fairly dead world mostly inhabited by people you can't talk to... and if you can you usually wish you couldn't since most of side-quests seem to be fetch quests or kill x animals. Clearing an encampment does change who patrols the area, but that seems to be the extent you can affect the island. Likewise, opening up communications just means you get more weapons for free. There are animals and pirates out in the world the world is pretty... but that does not make it feel alive. There is very little character to the island or the people there and therefore it is hard to care.The same story has the same problem with mostly unlikeable characters and poorly developed villains. Your only interaction with them is as they talk to you after capturing you for the 51th time. The main story line does give some missions that are somewhat fun (the ones that are pretty much specially designed encampment missions), but it is also mired in QTE's and tower segments. They also provide the only real challange in the game since they force you into fighting in the open and you sometimes have characters with you that are not allowed to die. Otherwise the game is very very easy, even on the highest setting. Actually, the only thing the higher setting seemed to do that I could tell was to add more enemies, make animals more powerful and speed up reinforcements. Which of course makes stealth even more important.Overall I enjoyed the gameplay and I would still recommend the game based on that. The boring character's and lackluster life of the island did take away some of the enjoyment though."
