,Recommended,220240,5541363,"Posted: 11 January, 2013",all,MℜSqƱifler®™,"Far Cry 3This review is subjective and entirely my own opinion, feel free to agree or disagree with it.Far Cry 3 may well be one of my favourite games, it is truly a great FPS with one of the best antagonists in gaming, although the plot leaves little to be desired.ProsAn amazing antagonist, Vass is truly terrifying.Fantastic shooting mechanics, all of the guns feel great and being able to customise them makes each gun feel unique.Rook Island looks and feels great. It has some gorgeous landscapes and brilliant wildlife.Driving is sufficient, it is neither good or bad.Great voice acting from all of the characters, although some cutscenes have strange audio bugs which will cause their audio levels to drop slightly.The world has some interesting history.Multiplayer, while now being extinct and generic was still very fun.Co-op campaign was very buggy for me and my friend, but it was amusing, a great addition but you won't kick yourself if you don't play it.Map editor is easy to use and a lot of fun, downloading user created maps can add so much more to the game.Great soundtrack, Brain Tyler did a very good job and there is a sequence that features a great song by Skrillex and Damien Marley.Great optimisation, which is very rare with a Ubisoft game. Plenty of options for adjusting the game and almost no drops below 60fps.ConsA few bugs and glitches.If you care about it the multiplayer and co-op are practically extinct. You may find other players for cooperative play on forums, though.SummaryThis game is great, whether you pay full price or buy it on a sale it is definitely worth the money. With some great characters, gorgeous graphics, responsive controls and a decent story you will easily get several hours out of this game."
