76561198014242486,Recommended,220240,34091303,Posted: 7 August,all,Polifimia,"Far Cry 3 comes in the acclaimed series starting with the original Far Cry, which was for its era a pioneering game. The third entry is a first-person shooter that combines elements of the original open-world of Far Cry, a huge variety of side quests a la GTA, with small touches of Tomb Raider and Assasin´s Creed.It manages to surpass the original in every aspect and manages to become a reference for this game kind.Pros:+ vast environment with tons of quests to do and places to explore by climbing, paragliding and swimming+ excellent graphics, effects and animations+ memorable villains and some very interesting secondary characters, all presented through well-thoughout dialogs and a main story with shocking and mature-oriented moments+ variety in arsenal, different play styles from stealth to full-gun blazing+ nice music (especially at the very end :)) and sound effects+ game duration can be tuned according to player, most quests are optional; tons of achievements and tasks for the completionistsCons:- some quests can become a bit repeated towards the end, same for the environment which always remains jungle-like- some parts of the main quest do not make a lot of sense.The friends are trying to escape through a boat which rests at the top of a mountain? What boat is this - Noah´s ark? Same for some ""cheap"" moments when the protagonist avoids death- music beat can be a bit distracting in some battle moments- second island is perhaps less interesting and challenging than the first one- connection to uplay is obligatory to play even if you open it through steamAll in all, a real gem and a must-play action game that defines the standards for the genre. This is how sequels should be made."
