76561198077257247,Recommended,220240,33192463,Posted: 3 July,all,Jugg3rNau7,the best
76561197972140596,Recommended,220240,13668530,"Posted: 28 December, 2014",all,Kelso,"If you follow games at all, you already know that Far Cry 3 is one of the best, most immersive single-player first-person shooters to come along in years. It combines a chilling story, thought-provoking themes, solid gunplay, beautiful graphics, an excellent soundtrack, and jam-packs all of them into an expansive and immersive open-world that is just as fun to explore as it is to kill baddies in.The intriguing main storyline will pull you in from the start. The main character undergoes a bone-chilling and believable transformation from a priveleged, pampered rich boy to an angry, ston-cold killer. The rest of the story is also full of complex and entertaining characters (not to mention one of the best villains in recent memory), and yet you will be just as pulled in by the opportunities to hunt, craft, kill pirates, liberate forts, and explore the beautiful Rook Island for side-quests, relics and assorted goodies that allow you to build up your skills and expand your arsenal.The combat, while far form the only draw, is exceptional. In this open-world, the choice is yours: would you prefer to go in stealthy, set-up shop on a tall hillside with your silenced sniper rifle, or go in guns blazing with a wide variety of SMGs, shotguns, assault rifles, and explosives? The shooting mechanics are very well done - the guns have a real punch to them - and there are plenty (30+) to choose from. The AI is also solid; your enemies will take cover, try to flank you, and will kill you easily if you play foolishly.The graphics are excellent, and the design of the island is beautiful. Water ripples in the moonlight, sun-rays glimmer on your screen, bullets ricochet to and fro, and explosions look and feel powerful - as do the after-burning effects that can quickly consume a small forest. The electronic soundtrack is also great: it ebbs and flows with combat, and becomes somber in more heartfelt moments. It's integrated excellently throughout the game - you won't often be able to tell it's there, but it will get your heart pumping.While exceptional, the game is not perfect. Exploration might have even been even better if the map was revealed more naturally instead of through radio towers, and I often found I had way too much money and not near enough to spend it on. The interface, crafting and customization options could also be improved. Still, as a whole, Far Cry 3 is a fantastic game that you will easily get 25-30+ hours out of and enjoy every minute of. There's much more that could be said, but this game is incredible value for anything less than $10, and you should really enjoy and explore the beatufiul but dangerous Rook Island for yourself!9.2/10"
