,Recommended,220240,8812449,"Posted: 22 January, 2014",all,AndyW_UK,"After spending 90+ hours completing everything there is to do in Far Cry 3, I can safely say I haven't had this much fun in an FPS for a long time. Having the freedom to do practically anything you like, in any order you like, in any style you like, is a refreshing change from the standard-fare modern military shooter. I had so much fun doing things like, when needing a vehicle, popping a jeep driver with my Desert Eagle .50, watching the jeep slide up a hill, flip over a few times, kill the gunner in the roll, and then land perfectly upright on the road in the direction I needed it. Thank you very much!However, the game does have a few caveats - firstly, it's as buggy as all hell, even today. Crashes to desktop on buying/selling items, restarting mission/quest checkpoints, or just entirely randomly while running around is worryingly common, so save often. I even fell through the ground and out of the world on the wingsuit once.The UI and save system is also somewhat irksome and could've been implemented better on PC (an unfortunate leftover of the inferior console version), and the cash limitation is absurd - once you've bought all the weapons, upgrades and paint jobs, the only way to spend your wallet is to deliberately burn ammo and get yourself injured to buy armour/medicine. Not a game-breaker by any means, but annoying for a completionist like myself who wants to loot every chest, but can't because of an arbitrary cash limit - it just doesn't need to be there.Finally, there are one or two poorly-balanced story missions that can be very difficult to complete unless you metagame it and do things like lay mines with advance knowledge of enemy spawn positions (Huntley and the plane repairs, I'm looking at you!). The plot could've done without some of the trippy, mystical stuff as well.Despite a fair few misgivings, though: overall decent shooting, interesting world, plenty of free-form fun, and some intriguing and dark characters make for an enjoyable game. Just don't expect it to be perfect."
