,Recommended,220240,9593448,"Posted: 22 March, 2014",all,Eishua,"I bought Far Cry 3 to got a good fps experience out of it. You don't see many of them these days. Back in the day FarCry 1 was a fps player´s dream with a lot of challenging shooter action. Well... Far Cry 3 is a very different game compared to it´s predecessors.Far Cry 3 is less of an fps game and more of a casual story game with stealthy experience gathering and item upgrade hoarding.  You start with only 1 weapon slot and you must find animals in order to craft more. The joke about this is that the game itself is ridicilously easy even on the most difficult setting. Sure you will have problems with your starting pistol, but after you get famas and mp5 with silencer (which is after 2 hours tops), the game turns into a cakewalk.The story line was good enough, but you are just a mindless spectator in it. There are also loads of unskippable cutscenes, where you can't do anything but turn your head and press mandatory buttons in order to get forward. You naturally don't have a say on how things proceed. Music and voice acting are mostly good. The main protagonis, Vaas, can even be commended.To sum it up, Far Cry 3 is a great casual (fps)-game, but if you want a challenging fps in your hands, this one will feel lacking in a lot of ways."
