,Recommended,220240,9802241,"Posted: 12 April, 2014",all,Cosmosis,"Far Cry 3 is an all around awesome, worthwhile experience.SINGLE PLAYER:The single player is the meat of the game, and it's a blast. The story is all-around enjoyable, despite a few hiccups, and it really helps to show you the full extents of what you can do in the game. For me personally, though, I enjoyed the free roam more. The island is beautiful, and the vegetation is lush. There is a nice amount of weapons, attachments and paint jobs to keep you interested. Once a weapon has been used, you can equip it for free at any vending machine in the game, which really allows you to try new things on the fly. Besides the standard weapons (Assault Rifles, SMGs, LMGs, Sniper Rifles & Shotguns), there are also a variety of unique weapons, including a flare gun, flamethrower and recurve bow, all of which help keep the game fresh. The hunting/crafting system could be a bit more fleshed out, as you will likely be nearly done crafting before even reaching the second island, and after crafting is done there is not much incentive to hunt. The core of the game, however, are the outposts. The outposts are definitely the most enjoyable part, and also allow you to really use all the weapons and equipment in interesting ways. As the outposts grow more and more complex the challenge becomes greater and greater to succesfully capture one, and the reward is always worth it. On a side note, the takedown system is also amazingly executed. It distances itself from the type of knifing prevalent in Call of Duty, and changes it up so that when you are within range (close range) it will go into a  little locked animation for the kill. It doesn't make the melee overpowered, but it makes for some awesome kills, especially when you jump off a ledge and land on an enemy.MULTIPLAYER:It may not be the focus of the game, but it is well done. A variety of interesting maps and fresh new modes (Firestorm and Transmission come to mind), it's a lot of fun. The unlock system works well, and there's also something called decoding -- after finishing a co-op chapter/multiplayer match, you can find encrypted data. After spending time putting it through a decoder (it decodes in the background) it can give you XP or Weapon Mods. Weapon Mods increase one aspect of a gun by a lot, while having some type of drawback. My only complaint with multiplayer is that higher end data sources take a fair bit of time to decode, with the biggest (Hard Drive) taking a solid 8 hours. This has been helped, though, by speed boosts. After you finish decoding something, you can usually send a speed boost to a friend of yours (no use to you). If you have lots of friends, you should receive lots of speed boosts which can make the waiting time much more bearable.Overall: Great game. Awesome single player, and fresh new multiplayer as well, Far Cry 3 gets a solid 9/10."
