76561198354864207,Recommended,220240,33349982,Posted: 7 July,all,DeadsecPool,"If I had to describe this game in one word, it would be art.Writing: 10/10 - superb. Though the overall premise is quite simple (stuck on island, must save friends), the execution is phenomenal, and you can truly empathize throughout the unpredictable twists and turns of this adventure. I spotted many writing techniques that added to the quality, such as a parallel episode at the end of which truly showcased the character development of Jason. For a person who deems writing as an essential quality to a great game, this game is impressive. Certainly better than many movies, tv shows, video games, and books of the genre.Gameplay: 9.8/10 - A game which truly lets you tackle objectives in your own way. And a skill tree that reflects that. A surprisingly good stealth system, weapons of which you can feel the impact, superb quality. My only gripes are that you have to be in the air a bit to long before deploying the wingsuit, thus if attempting to wingsuit down a hill that isn't 90 degrees, you might just land on the ground before deploying the wingsuit. Also, once you die, if you collected a bunch of loot, upgraded, finally killed that tiger before you saved, its all gone once you respawn. Once you achieve something, save.In conclusion: 10/10 masterpiece"
