76561198033357842,Not Recommended,220240,22070863,"Posted: 26 March, 2016",all,Your racist uncle [SALTZGOD],"A lot of people think this is a good game. It's not.First off, you only have access to a few weapons, certainly not more than 20. This isn't weapon types, or weapons that you can buy different models of. Just 20 weapons, period. And they're terribly easy to get. Within 1 hour of starting the game, I had access to the assault rifle I used for literally THE REST OF THE GAME. The combat is also pretty stupid since you face the exact same enemies over and over and over again. All in all, combat gets repetitive enough that you actually hope no enemies show up. IN AN FPS.You gain xp (?) from getting to checkpoints in the story which unlocks skills periodically. They're not impressive and are mostly useless, and I'm confident you could beat the entire game without ever looking at the skill tree. As an example, there's a skill that lets you assassinate an enemy from below by climbing onto the ledge they're stanging on. It sounds badass, but the opportunity to do this comes up only like twice in the whole game.To be fair, the visuals and exploration system are the highlights of this game. There's nothing quite like going to the highest point in the map and jumping off with a hang glider. You can also explore caves and abandoned Japanese bunkers to find relics and other crap that gives you the history of the island. All that stuff is marked on your map though, so there's no real exploration going on.Finally, this game has NO replay value at all. It's totally linear except for the ending cutscene (you can choose one of two endings, both of which are anticlimactic). Apart from that, you have no choices to make and no way to influence the story. If you were dumb enough to play this game again, you would have to do all the same stuff you did the first time around, just to get to one alternate 30-second cutscene.You'd be better off buying skyrim, which has crazy replay value, and watching the cutscenes from far cry on youtube. That would give you the full experience of this game without costing a cent."
