,Recommended,220240,8477365,"Posted: 1 January, 2014",all,4th,"I'd say this was the best game I played in 2013, but as it came out in 2012, I'm gonna go ahead and say it is one of the best games I've played in 2012 as well as 2012. Great story, great gameplay, great music. All comes together to give you some of the best experiences you'll have in gaming, and I can say that without a doubt. Steal system was excellent too.Presentation: 10/10 - Nothing that I noticed could have been improved.Graphics: 10/10 - Even for it's time, this game has outstanding graphics. If you have the rig for it, pump it up to max graphics and you will be in for a ****ing treat.Sound: 9/10 - The music in this game is fantastic, and there is nothing scarier than trecking through the jungle only to hear a leopard or something of the sort nearby. Some of the weirdest music pieces have been used in some situations, but that adds to the charm. Weird doesn't necessarily = bad, mind you.Gameplay: 9.5/10 - The shooting, the running, the falling, the swimming, the stealthing, the rock throwing, the bow mechanics, everything. Oh and did I mention you will be able to go cliffjumping?Lasting Appeal: 9/10 - As far as the multiplayer goes, that left a little to be desired but honestly it was still pretty decent. I had fun for a few hours running around shooting people, similarly to titles like Call of Duty, etc, but with a few twists on the gameplay. If you have a few friends to play with in a deathmatch or even the co-op missions I wasn't honestly very fond of, and you will have yourself some fun times with this game after finishing the story. Hell, you may even want to repeat the story like a lot of my friends have on a higher difficulty. Definitely a lot of replayability here."
