76561198190431418,Not Recommended,220240,29550514,Posted: 28 January,all,mikeymike226,"Amazing game, and without a doubt, one of my all-time favorites.  A loot-shooter with TONS of things to do, and a huge island to explore.  I probably did 2 or 3 playthroughs on console, and after recently building a new gaming PC, I decided I wanted to raise hell on Rook Island once more.My only knock (and a big one) on the PC version of this game is that it crashes without warning CONSTANTLY, and I have no idea why just yet.  When the game was released, Windows 10 was obviously not in existence yet so there is some sort of issue having to do with the operating system.  I've researced some boards in an effort to troubleshoot, and from what I can gather there is something with Windows 10 that isn't playing nicely with FC3.  The problem is that people have suggested about 100 different ways to pinpoint and ultimately fix the issue.  Whatever the reason, it's pretty frustrating and I don't feel like spending hours troubleshooting this when I could spend what little spare time I have to play something else.  As great as this game is and as much as I love it, I'm kind of regretting the purchase and thinking of abandoning it altogether.If you choose to purchase the game, I'd recommend looking into these issues first to spare yourself a TON of frustration and wasted time.  I've lost track how many times I've completed a mission or liberated an outpost only to have the game crash immediatley afterwards without saving my progress.  Unless you know for certain you can pinpoint and resolve whatever is causing the game to crash, I'd probably recommend that you pass on this game for PC.  If you have a legacy console (PS3 or XB360) you'd be much better off playing it on one of those.  I've been hoping that this game would be made backward compatible for XB1, but sadly that hasn't happened yet."
