,Recommended,220240,9581486,"Posted: 21 March, 2014",all,Knexus,"Farcry 3 does a lot of things right and a few things wrong.Let's start with the positives.  The sandbox open world is absolutely beautiful.  It's massive, it's lush, and you'll always see the islanders out and about doing things so it really gives the world a sense of life.  Out of curiousity, I turned my graphics settings down to low and the game still looked pretty damn good.   I wasn't much of a fan of the music in the game, as most of it was very basic beats, but the ambient noises are excellent and you'll always have that paranoid feeling when you hear that tiger growl off in the distance, not knowing whether it's coming after you or just passing by.Now the negatives.  The side missions can be quite repetitive.  They fall into the formula of ""Go hunt this animal or Kill this guy with a knife or deliver these supplies before the time runs out.""  It was hard for me not to get bored at times doing the side missions, because I've already done some redition of previously.  The main campaign was pretty good.  Not excellent, not just okay, but somewhere in between.  The story has a lot to be desired but luckily it's held up by an excellent voice actor cast.The crafting and skill system is pretty cool.  My only complaint is I had a tendancy to have all my skills filled before the next set would open up, which is dependent on your main story progression.  So there would be times where I would have 3-4 skill ponts I couldn't use because the additional skills were still locked because I hadn't made it that far in the story yet.The game has a few quirks, but overall was a very enjoyable experience.  If your a completionist, then there are tons and tons of things for you to collect and complete.  Playing just through the main story took me somewhere along the lines of 18(ish) hours, but if you strive to do everything, I would be surprised if you could easily get 35+ hours of gameplay.  I recommend Far Cry 3 who like first person shooters and sandbox worlds.  There is tons for you to explore and story will keep you interested(just perhaps not on the edge of your seat).I am giving the Far Cry 3 an 8/10."
