,Recommended,220240,9509230,"Posted: 16 March, 2014",all,Razevoir,"Excellent shooter on almost every front.  This game brings strong mechanics, polished visuals, and satisfying gunplay to the table, along with one of the best villains you'll encounter in any game on the market.  Never dull, never a shortage of things to do, you can spend 30+ hours in its single player open world alone, and it also includes co-op and multiplayer for players who are interested in that kind of thing.  The only obvious shortcoming I found in it was somewhat inferior audio engineering, but the rest of the game is so well put together that it's easily excusable.  The game provides enormous amounts of new content for people who like to rush stories, plenty of toys for those that like to mess with its sandbox, and lots of objectives to satisfy completionists.  Top it all off with a superior PC port with excellent optimization and extra bells and whistles, there is no excuse for fans of PC shooters to not purchase this game."
