,Not Recommended,220240,1851329,"Posted: 23 April, 2013",all,Meezermouzer,"Far Cry 3 is better than its predecessors but claiming it's ""Elder Scrolls with guns"" is hyperbole at BEST. The game has a beautiful world, yet it's shallow and sparse--lacking true believability or detail. This leaves the player feeling empty and unmotivated; having no emotional attachment with the world or its characters--something one wouldn't expect from an open-ended world. Far Cry 3 takes place on an island that consists mostly of wilderness with a few small shanty villages and pirate outposts that you can ""liberate"". The game has some brief adrenaline-pumping sequences but it is ultimately a generic FPS through and through. Granted, it does have a light mixture of other elements like weapon customization, skill trees, and crafting. However these options don't make combat any less repetitive or the quests any less tedious. The story develops in traditional, albeit questionable ways and side missions and challenges are laughable and boring. I wouldn't recommend this game for $30 (which is what I paid for it). I would wait for a better deal. I know there are people out there who enjoyed Far Cry 3, but I'm not one of them."
