,Not Recommended,220240,15575404,"Posted: 26 April, 2015",all,Vernichtungsoperator,"I am too old for this.The graphics are great, the combat is fun, the enemies act quite intelligent for NPCs. FC3 is not a bad game per se. But the story ruined it all.The intro is like a trailer, short scenes with short glimpses into the life of some ""other people"" with whom you don't identify. Over-the-top cliche US-american tourists acting and being stupid.I grant the game its very good moments. The first ""level"" is quite nice and probably one of the nicest and most fun mandatory tutorial-level ever made. There are some other moments in the game where you just go ""whooooaa"", the music perfectly supports the feeling and you see the genius of whoever designed this one.But then: No one I know who played the game identified with the character. Or felt even sympathetic to the cause. Frankly, I forgot what the hell I was trying to do in the end. Then the game reminds you: aha. I don't care for this person.Your own alter ego's transformation from a whimsical tourist to a brawly ""man"" by the means of hunting, killing and related survival skills of the jungle seems cliche as well, but under the circumstances of being stranded in the jungle actually feels alright.Because of this transformation, you alienate your old friends over time. In the end, you get to make a decision: And the game ruins it again. It suddenly acts like a childs movie again, where there is obviously just one ""right"" decision and you get punished for the other. Even worse, the punishing doesn't even make sense and seems very last-minute design-changey.General Gameplay: Well done combat, thats what hooked me in the game. But there is some typical grinding stuff that just gets boring. The typical ubisoft ""climb the tower to reveal more map and then leap down into the hay"". Oh wait, that was the other game.. you zipline off the tower. Then some base capturing to gain spawn points and map influence. After the 15th camp you know every camp-prop, door, or hut-design by heart and start hating the game designers for that cheap gametime trick. But after the 50th camp its not really necessary anyway. You are so strong, you can just waltz by and shoot anyone who bothers. Clean that camp? Ain't got no time for that s...The problem of FC3 in short: It starts well and ticks so many boxes, but then negates all the effort by obviously trying to appeal to a maximum audience. It does that by dumbing it down so hard that all the effort of the game is not just wasted, but you as an at least half-brained intelligent player are feeling insulted. Probably one of the worst cases of wasted potential I have ever seen in the game. Just imagine what would have resulted, had the story designers wandered into, for example, Gabe's office."
