,Recommended,220240,12508944,"Posted: 16 October, 2014",all,NickBlasta,"Pleasantly surprised is probably my general feeling about this game- it's okay, but not great, except as compared to its thoroughly awful predecessor, Far Cry 2. FC3 is an open-world sandbox game set on a fictional Pacific island, populated by various missions, time trials, a buttload of item collecting quests and a general overarching plot.The plot is basically that of a 90s action movie. You play a California Bro, out exploring Asia with the rest of his Bros and Broettes, who decide to end their vacation by parachuting onto a picturesque island in an x-treme fashion.  You and your bros are captured, abused, you escape and you embark on an adventure to free your friends, to find yourself, and to get even. Etc.It suffers like most open-world games in that a lot of attention is placed either in developing the world or fleshing out the gameplay, but not usually both. In this case there is really little of note to do- most of the missions involve killing waves of dozens of identical soldiers before you can proceed to the next. There are a few standouts like the famous weed-farm burn mission, where you light up a marijuana plantation with a flamethrower while Skrillex blasts over the violence, but for the most part, the game is a sequence of boring set pieces that never quite satisfies. If you love pointless item collecting there's a ♥♥♥♥ing ton of it. I don't.It's a ♥♥♥♥ing pretty game though, especially when you have a computer capable of cranking the graphics options (this is of course a Crytek engine) and it's really easy to feel like you're actually in the jungle wandering around the island. The sound DESIGN is okay, but tends to be populated by the three repetitive voice files your cardboard enemies say.It's a decent play. Everyone probably owns this already, but if you want to experience the star of 2012, go for it."
