76561198141004242,Recommended,220240,26153264,"Posted: 21 October, 2016",all,jackoff,"If you're into great graphics, low requirements, an outstanding story line, and a breathtaking exeperience, then Far Cry 3 my friend, is the game for you.Even now, after I've completed it already a few months back, I still think about this game every now and again or when ever I glance at it in my library, I think about how good it is in general. It's just one of those games you can play over, and over, and over again without getting bored. Even if you do get bored with the story, there are tonnes of things available around the island to do that are extremely entertaining, like discovering the ancient stories and finding relics in underground temples, or racing against the clock to deliver a package, discovering new areas to explore by (hacking?) a radio tower, and best of all, hostile take overs. Not only just rewarding money, guns, xp and teleporting locations, it offers even MORE jobs to look at, like hunting or assasination.This was perhaps the last good game in the Far Cry Series, just before the okay-ish Far Cry 4, and the seriously disappointing Far Cry Primal. I'm sure nearly everyone agrees with this.I mean, seriously. What's better than blowing up and burning millions of dollars worth of weed at a farm?"
